title: rice pudding
directions: In a large pan, cook all together; simmer for 1 hour. Put into shallow dish and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg. Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: bacon-cheese breakfast brunch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: ugly dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pan.
Spread chili over cream cheese. Pour salsa over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: pepper-poppy seed pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray tube pan or Bundt pan heavily with nonstick cooking spray (pan should hold 6 cups).
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
With electric beaters, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs in one at a time and beat well.
Stir in lemon juice and extract.
Beat in dry ingredients. Fold in poppy seed.
Spread in pan and bake slowly at 325° for an hour, or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into middle of cake.
Cool on rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and let stand covered, overnight, before serving.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add the marshmallows, keeping the liquid hot until marshmallows dissolve.
Allow mixture to cool.
Mix celery, nuts and cream cheese in a bowl.
Add salad dressing and mix well.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir.
Add jello mixture and mix thoroughly.
Chill until mixture starts to mound on a spoon.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate several hours or overnight until set.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown beef roast.
Add bouillon, peppercorns and oregano. Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Slice thinly.
Serve on buns.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 appetizers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a dish.
Set aside.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving portions.
Mix flour and salt; pound into meat.
Brown meat in small amount of hot shortening.
Place meat in shallow baking dish.
Blend remaining flour with drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over meat; cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Top with cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and spread 1/2 the mixture in a 9 x 9 inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Then spread over chilled gelatin, 6 oz softened cream cheese and 1 cup sour cream, which has been creamed together.
Add remaining salad mixture and re-chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve.
Serves 12.

title: old fashioned chicken dumplings
directions: Cut shortening into flour, mixed with baking powder and salt. Use milk to make a stiff dough (3/4 cup is sufficient).
Shape into dumplings by rolling very thin and cut as desired.
Drop into boiling chicken broth and cook 12 to 15 minutes, slowly.
Cook in covered pot, but do not stir or remove from pot until ready to serve.

title: never fail fruit cake
directions: Dredge 3/4 cup flour into cut up fruit and cut up nuts.
Set aside.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add figs and dry ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until done.
Can be baked in tube or Bundt pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Sprinkle Veg-All vegetables over top.
Bring soup and broth to a boil.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Combine flour, oleo and buttermilk. Spread or spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix cornbread mix and stuffing mix together.
Add crumbled bread.
Mix butter, onions and celery together.
Add to bread mixture.
Add broth to make a soft mixture.
Add chopped eggs, salt and pepper.
Also, if you like, add a dash of sage.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a flat cooking pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: modeling dough(kid's sake)
directions: Mix together in a saucepan flour, salt and alum.
Boil water and salad oil in another pan.
Pour over dry mixture.
Mix well. Knead when cool.
Add choice of food colors.
Store in tight container.
This is fun stuff.
Try it with the kids.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil until done.
Cool, peel and mash.
Add sugar and salt.
Make into patties like small hamburgers; flatten out.
Put large marshmallow in center.
Put another patty on top. Press edges together.
Press into graham cracker crumbs on both sides.
Fry in skillet with a little margarine on both sides until brown.
Cool slowly until marshmallow sets.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop sherbet into punch bowl.
Pour chilled pop into punch bowl.
Ladle into punch cups.

title: sausage and cheese log
directions: Mix all together; form into 4 to 6 logs.
Wrap with Saran Wrap; place in freezer bag.
Freeze and have ready for unexpected guests.
Remove from freezer, slice and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: farmer's ribs
directions: Blanch ribs in a large kettle of simmering water for 30 minutes. Drain. While ribs blanch, in a large saucepan, cook the onions and garlic in the butter over low heat, stirring, for 15 minutes until softened. Add the tomato sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and chili paste, if desired. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Arrange ribs in a shallow baking dish. Spoon sauce over the ribs. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Brush with sauce. Bake 20 minutes more. Turn meat over. Brush again with sauce and bake another 20 minutes. Serve hot or slightly cooled.

title: german sausage balls
directions: Roll into balls.
Roll in egg, then in crushed Ritz crackers. Fry slowly until done.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion, relish and poppy seed with ham and cheese pieces. Spread thickly on both sides of buns. Wrap in foil and bake until warm. Can also use smaller rolls, even dinner rolls and serve as appetizers.

title: breakfast casserole(good for a crowd)
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and mustard.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream 1/2 shortening, 1 cup sugar.
Add 1 egg, blend well.
Add flour mixture and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon full on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes (do not over bake).
Remove from oven and press 1/2 marshmallow (cut side down); return to oven and bake 2 minutes more.
When cool ice with chocolate icing.

title: great grandma lillie lemmon's spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift an ample amount of Softasilk cake flour onto a square of paper.
Measure and sift first 4 ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Make a well and add in order the oil, egg yolks, cold water, vanilla and lemon rind.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Measure eggs whites and cream of tartar into a large mixing bowl.
Whip until whites form very still peaks.
Do not underbeat!
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over whipped egg whites, gently folding with rubber scraper just until blended.
Do not stir!
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan 4-inches deep immediately.
Bake for 55 minutes in a slow moderate oven (325°), then increase to moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 15 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Immediately turn pan upside down, placing tube part over neck of funnel or bottle.
Let hang, free of table, until cold.
Loosen from sides and tube with spatula.
Turn pan over and hit edge sharply on table to loosen.

title: oven-fried sesame chicken
directions: Place soy sauce in a shallow dish.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Remove chicken from soy sauce; discard soy sauce.

title: muffin donuts
directions: Beat all ingredients together and put into muffin cups.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Dip into melted butter, then in a cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Makes 15 donuts.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients and 3 tablespoons of bacon grease and 3 strips of uncooked bacon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into ungreased 9 X 13 pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place ingredients in greased casserole.
Grate sharp cheese over top last 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(May be halved.)

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and baking soda; stir and allow to become foamy.
Set aside.
Sift flour and then measure amount needed for recipe.
Add baking powder to flour and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla, buttermilk and salt; mix.
Add flour mixture a little at a time; beat well.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Cool.
Frost with Seven Minute Frosting.

title: baked tuna fish and noodles(no. g-33)
directions: Add noodles to boiling, salted water.
Boil 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine noodles, celery, onions, pimiento, corn flakes, salt, pepper, tuna fish and fish liquid and oil.
Mix melted fat and flour; stir until smooth.
Mix milk and water; add to flour mixture.
Heat to boiling point.
Boil 5 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over fish and noodle mixture; mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 40 minutes.
Yields 100 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: pizza spaghetti casserole
directions: Place spaghetti in buttered 9 x 12 baking dish. Pour 15 ounce can of tomato sauce over spaghetti. Brown beef with oregano; drain and sprinkle over sauce. Layer with mushrooms, olives, onions and pepperoni. Pour 8 ounce can tomato sauce over all. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Mix margarine, flour, vanilla, pecans and powdered sugar. Shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Crumble 1 stack Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Make a cream sauce with the butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Put salmon into bowl and add the sauce and lemon juice; mix well with fork until salmon is well broken.
Set aside and when cold, mold into desired shapes; roll in bread crumbs, then dip in egg, beaten with 1 tablespoon cold milk, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep hot fat.

title: 12 hour salad
directions: Put in double boiler and cook until thick - eggs, lemon juice, and sugar.

title: pan rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water; let stand a few minutes, then stir until dissolved.
Pour hot milk over butter.
Add sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, eggs and half the flour.
Beat well. Add enough more flour to make a dough that will not stick to bowl. Turn out on a floured board and knead lightly.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and turn down on board.
Shape into balls.
Let rise until double.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 425° approximately 20 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Mix sauteed onion, flour, ham and cheese and spread in pie shell.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the mixture in the pie shell.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes. Do not overcook.
Let set about 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add alternately the milk and the flour.
Add flavoring.
Mix well. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Stir in rolled oats, walnuts and dates.
Combine the beaten egg, sugar, sour cream and molasses.
Beat well. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Place in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from dish and cool on rack. Cut in thin slices to serve.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: soy-ginger steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass bowl.
Pour over meat that has been placed in a glass dish.
Marinate meat for 6 to 8 hours, turning meat every 1 to 2 hours.

title: reunion cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into ball and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: pecan drops
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter with electric mixer at medium speed about 30 seconds.
Add powdered sugar, about half the flour and half of milk and the vanilla to the butter.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour and milk.
Stir in nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Lightly press a pecan half on top of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie rack. Makes 48 cookies.

title: italian dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Shake before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat and onion until crispy brown.
Drain well.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Serve on buns.

title: butterscotch krispie treats
directions: Combine butterscotch chips and butter in a 2-quart glass dish. Cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes, at power control 7, until melted.
Stir in marshmallows.
Cook, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes, at power control 7, until marshmallows are softened; stir until smooth.
Stir in cereal.
Press into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch square glass baking dish.
Let stand until cool and set; cut into squares.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries to gelatin mixture; stir as they dissolve.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Place 1/2 of mixture in dish; chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over chilled layer.
Add remaining strawberry mixture; chill until firm.
If not using promptly, banana slices should be dipped in lemon juice to prevent darkening.
NutraSweet gelatin may be used.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs on all sides.
Brown onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly until flavors are blended, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour sauce over spareribs.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done at 350°.

title: ethel whitt's lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender, except egg whites. Cook mixture in double boiler until thick, stirring several times. Pour into a cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, spread on pie and bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Cut candied fruit into small pieces. Mix all ingredients except milk and marshmallows.
Melt marshmallows in milk and mix with other ingredients.
When well mixed, pack in buttered Bundt pan or small loaf pan.
When cool, remove from pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces and put in bottom of casserole dish. Sprinkle with pepper and garlic powder. Mix sour cream and soup. Pour over casserole. Melt oleo with broth; add stuffing. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with sour cream until smooth.
Mix in 1/2 jar taco sauce.
Spread mixture into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Take rest of taco sauce and spread over top of mixture evenly, then layer tomatoes (chopped) with chopped lettuce and Cheddar cheese on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chops with noodles
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in oil.
Place in a baking dish.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add onion, ketchup and water to noodles.
Mix together and spread over pork chops.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top has browned. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mayo cookies
directions: Combine mayo and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: dessert or pies
directions: Sift flour and salt in a large bowl.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles small peas.
Add water and butter flavoring; toss with fork until moistened and mixture starts to form a ball. Gather dough into a ball; divide in half. On a lightly floured surface, roll out 1
portion to 1/8-inch thickness.
Using plastic lid or plate as a guide, cut into four 6-inch circles. Repeat with remaining dough.
Gently knead scraps together.
Roll out and cut 2 more circles to make a total of 10.

title: tom thumb cookies
directions: Combine shortening and salt.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup flour.
Press into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla to beaten eggs.
Beat until thick and foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons flour, baking powder, salt, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread over baked mixture.
Return to oven and bake an additional 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: vat-bollen(or ole cookin)
directions: Scald
milk.
Let cool; when lukewarm, add yeast dissolved in a little warm water.
Add
sugar,
salt, shortening,
raisins,
eggs and enough flour to make a soft batter.
Takes about 7 to 8 cups flour.
Let rise until double the amount.
Cut down, then fry in deep fryer.
Drop by tablespoon in deep fryer, dipping spoon in cold water each time to prevent batter sticking to spoon.
Turn dough balls over and fry for only a few minutes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon or powdered sugar.
Makes about 60.

title: meat loaf 1
directions: With clean hands, mix egg with ground beef in a bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hungarian macaroni and cheese
directions: Reserve liquid from mushrooms and pimento.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk; mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Pour in prebaked pie shell or graham cracker shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 8 x 14-inch casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz and rice. Season well.
Add celery, onion and butter.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs (crushed saltine crackers are a good substitute).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: frank's after school snack
directions: Frank Hart's Grandma Gregory taught Frank to make this for an afternoon snack when school was over.
It sounds different and looks different, but the taste is unique.

title: cheesy meat loaf (needs no gravy)(hot or cold)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until onion is soft. Remove from heat and mix with other ingredients.
Blend well. Shape into loaf and place into 10 x 14-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend together in blender until creamy.

title: shrimp quiches
directions: Generously grease small cup muffin pan.
Separate rolls into 12 equal pieces.
Cut each in half; press each half into bottom and sides of muffin cup.
Divide shrimp evenly among pastry shells.
Beat together egg, cream, onion, salt, dill and cayenne until well blended.
Using about 2 teaspoons for each, divide among shells, sprinkling cheese over tops.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20
minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool 5 minutes to serve warm.

title: layered cornbread and ham salad
directions: Stir dressing and buttermilk until well blended. Use a 3-quart bowl and layer 1/2 of all ingredients. Then put 1/2 of dressing mixture. Repeat with remaining ingredients and finish with the rest of the dressing mixture. Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: miss sue's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the first six ingredients.
Mix in flour.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking pan.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes (cookies won't appear done).
Remove from oven and let cool before removing from pan.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix flour, oats, cinnamon and set side.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix pumpkin and flour mixture alternately.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop a spoonful onto a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix together, except butter.
Put butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Put fruit in cake pan (fresh, frozen or canned).
Add tapioca or flour to thicken juice.
Put in oven to heat until topping is made.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni, following box directions.
Drain and place in buttered casserole dish.
Pour in small can of tomato sauce and mix.

title: fiddle faddle
directions: In a large, buttered bowl mix popcorn and peanuts.
In a heavy saucepan cook sugar, Karo and margarine.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn mixture and stir until mixture sticks together.
Spread into a large flat lightly greased pan and cool. Break in pieces to serve.

title: dinner cut casserole
directions: Saute fresh mushrooms and onion.
Place with gluten in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Cover with sauce made from remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexicali layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in large bowl (or container). After lettuce is added, drizzle dressing over top.
Completely cover (this will drain through veggies).
After chilling for an hour, add cheese to top and garnish with olives, peppers and paprika and crushed chips around to edge of salad.
Serves a bunch.
Serve with remaining chips.

title: strawberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Combine cookie mix, lemon peel and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Add contents of buttery flavor packet from mix and egg white.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Press half of the dough into pan.
Spread with preserves.
Make ropes with remaining dough to form lattice top over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 32 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars.
Yields 16 bars.

title: icebox cake
directions: Mix together well the butter, egg and sugar.
Fold in drained pineapple and nuts.
Layer dish or bowl with cracker crumbs.
Add filling; add whipped cream.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Serve chilled (approximately 2 hours).

title: apple shaped red beet eggs
directions: *Or 1 cup vinegar, 2 cups water and red food coloring.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook to almost done. Cut bacon in small bits and fry crispy.
Into bacon drippings, fry onions. After onions are done, mix water, vinegar and sugar to onion mix and put in green peppers.
Cook until boiling. Thicken slightly with cornstarch, then add bacon and potatoes.
Taste to see if you need more sugar or vinegar or salt.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together and fry.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Place broth and tomatoes in crock-pot.
Start on high. Meanwhile saute beef, onion and pepper.
Add frozen vegetables, remaining chopped vegetables and sauteed ingredients.
Reduce heat to low setting.
Simmer 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with crusty bread or biscuits.
Bon appetite!

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 2 ingredients until smooth. Slowly add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: chow mein
directions: String peas, slice onions, slice mushrooms, cut celery diagonally and cut flank or pork across the grain and then into small pieces.
Marinate meat in a mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce, pepper, salt, sugar, sherry and 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Mix 1 cup water, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce and set aside.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Brown meat. Add onion and rest of ingredients. Stir and cook for a few minutes. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: easy twice baked potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions, using only milk, instead of water.
Let set up a few minutes.
Add sour cream, 6 oz. of cheese and bacon bits.
Put entire mixture into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Liberally grease a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Press crumbs over bottom and sides.
In a large bowl, at high speed, beat cream cheese with cottage cheese.
Gradually beat in sugar, then eggs until well blended.
At low speed, beat in cornstarch, flour, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add melted butter and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes (center will be soft).
Turn off oven and let remain for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door!
After 2 hours, remove from oven. Cool and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: red raspberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except Chambord liqueur and lemon juice; stir on moderate heat until boiling, then add the liqueur and lemon juice.
Simmer 10 more minutes gently.
Serve on ice cream; especially great for peach melba.

title: barbecue
directions: Pressure cook chuck roast until tender (let cool).
Take off fat from meat.
Tear into small pieces (set aside broth).
Put meat back into pressure and add all ingredients.
Use enough broth to keep barbecue from being dry.
Blend well and cook.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook the noodles for 8 minutes.
Brown the hamburg in the olive oil.
Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, onion, pepper and oregano.
Place noodles in large pan or casserole.
Add sauce. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot pineapple dish
directions: Mix together in a bowl the crushed pineapple, eggs, flour and sugar.
Place in a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Melt the butter in a saucepan and shred the bread into it.
Spread this mixture over the pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked fudge
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until crusty on top, but soft inside. Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add corn.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add to corn and egg.
Drop by tablespoons in hot oil.
Fry until brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook
potatoes until almost tender and drain.
Add sour cream, soup,
cheese
and
onion.
Crumble
Ritz	crackers in plastic bag;
add
to
melted margarine.
Pour potato mixture into casserole dish and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.	Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs to make a crust.
Place in freezer.
Beat the cream cheese, margarine, eggs and sugar.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over mixture; drain pineapple and pour over bananas. Cover with Cool Whip, nuts and maraschino cherries.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: crock-pot pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops.
Combine chops, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Cook 1/2 hour on high, 3 hours on medium.
Good with biscuits.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: In 2 quarts water (boiling) cook broccoli or steam in less water.
Drain (hold water aside).
In a skillet mince 2 cloves garlic very small.
On a low flame and in 1/4 cup oil, cook until tender and lightly browned.
Add cut up broccoli bits, salt and pepper.
In a large pot boil spaghetti until tender; drain.
Add broccoli to spaghetti.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Some held over broccoli liquid can be added if less drier is desired.

title: o-so-good raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add eggs last.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven 5 minutes and medium oven 30 minutes.

title: spinach supper ring
directions: Let
dough
rise
until doubled.
Preheat oven to 350°. Roll and pat out dough to a 10 x 15-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle spinach, pepperoni,	mushrooms,
cheese and tomato paste over bread.
Roll up,
pinching
seams to seal sides.
Form a ring and
seal ends. Place in a greased and floured 10-inch pie or cake	pan,
seam side
down.
Bake
30 to 40 minutes or until nicely brown.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Slice package of dinner rolls in half.
Spread with Dijon mustard.
Add ham and cheese slices.
Replace top.
Melt together butter, poppy seed, dry mustard, onion flakes and Worcestershire. Pour over rolls.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: uncle earl's health bread
directions: Boil the raisins and water 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix by hand all other ingredients.
Add cooled raisins. Spoon into greased and floured bread tins. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: easy flaky wesson pastry dough
directions: Mix milk and oil.
Beat with a fork for 1 minute.
Sift flour, sugar and salt into a medium size mixing bowl. Pour liquid into middle of dry mixture.
Stir with fork until moistened and put into 9-inch pie pan.
Good for one crust pies.

title: hotel cole slaw
directions: Wash, drain, dry and shred cabbage.
Place shredded cabbage in large bowl and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Must be well chilled.
Mix remaining ingredients in order given.
Toss dressing with cabbage and chill again before serving.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
Grate cheese; chop onion.
Heat tomato juice and chili mix.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Dip tortilla in juice until warm.
Spoon meat, some onion and some cheese in tortilla.
Roll. Place in pan.
Continue until all tortillas are rolled and placed in pan.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix flour and other dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter or margarine with a pastry blender until finely mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: pepper steak
directions: Marinate steak in 1/2 bottle of soy sauce.
Let stand for several minutes.
Flour and brown steak in skillet with small amount of oil.
Add peppers, tomatoes and onions, Worcestershire sauce and other 1/2 bottle soy sauce.
Cook slowly about 1 hour. Serve over rice.

title: elva green's version of chicken cacciatore
directions: Use a Dutch oven type pot.
Put dark pieces of chicken in pot along with all other ingredients except for white meat.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, then add the white pieces of chicken.
Cook for approximately 1 to 1 1/4 hours until meat is tender.
Remove bay leaf before eating.
This recipe may be enjoyed alone, with noodles or over rice.
Have a green salad with it.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare 1 day ahead.
Mix spaghetti, olives, salami, 1/2 bottle Italian dressing and 1/2 salad seasoning.
Next day, at least 4 hours before serving, add to mixture of cucumbers, tomatoes, remaining Italian dressing and salad seasoning salt.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cloves and cinnamon. Make a hole in the center and add baby food, oil, eggs, vanilla, coconut and pecans; mix well with spoon. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Remove from oven and turn out on a plate. Punch holes in cake and pour sauce over hot cake.

title: 5 soup hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Put into large casserole.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Fold in 2/3 of noodles and top with remaining noodles.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: wackey chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: angel's delight
directions: Beat whipped topping mix with milk, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla until mixture thickens.
Set aside.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan or dish, layer angel food cake and cherry pie filling.
Pour over the layers the whipped topping mix.
Spoon Cool Whip on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: garden slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, leeks, chives and parsley flakes.
Mix yogurt, mustard, dill and salt.
Pour over slaw mixture; toss. Pepper to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: apple nut loaf
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes clean.

title: chicken taquitas
directions: Cook chicken until tender; debone and shred into bite size pieces.
Saute shredded chicken in 3 tablespoons oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in skillet.
Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons chicken mixture in each tortilla and roll.
Place tortilla seam side down in hot oil.
When tortilla seam is sealed and bottom is crispy, turn over and cook other side.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: savory tuna bake
directions: Steam celery, pepper and onion together for 15 minutes until slightly tender.
Set aside.
Melt butter and blend with flour, mustard, broth and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in one cup of cheese and remaining ingredients, including the steamed vegetable.
Turn into a greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cup of cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: sandra's salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
May add coconut.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sour cream, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix in sugar, then add remaining dry ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
(Dough is quite soft.)
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost when cooled.

title: sweet 'n sour baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fig ambrosia
directions: Gently mix together figs, mandarins and coconut.
Add mandarin juice, peel and sugar.
Chill.
This must be served the same day it is prepared.
Serves 4.

title: fruit chews
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and flour.
Fold in nuts and fruit.
Spread in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares.
Roll in 4x sugar.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites stiff or
until
they will not fall out of bowl.
Boil sugar and water until soft ball forms in water. Pour small amount over egg
whites.
Boil
some	more and pour over egg whites.
Continue
the process until last syrup forms a hard ball. Add remaining
syrup
to egg whites.
Beat until the gloss is gone.
Drop
on
waxed
paper
by tablespoonfuls. Pecans can be added just before the glossiness is gone.

title: st. florence super punch
directions: Prepare lemonade and orange juice according to directions on each can.
Pour into a large punch bowl; stir well.
Add Hawaiian Punch and pineapple juice; stir well.
Just before serving, add ice block.
Add ginger ale; pour down side of bowl to prevent splattering.
Stir well.
Add sherbet.
Serve.

title: easy almond bars
directions: Heat syrup and sugar until sugar melts and mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in almond extract.
Add to cereal and almonds.
Stir until well coated.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and buttermilk in a small bowl.
Pour out on a floured cutting board.
Knead until stiff.
Cut out in size that you prefer.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Place the chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with slices of Swiss cheese.
Combine the soup and wine; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle croutons over top; drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pudding and pineapple juice until smooth and well blended.
Fold in drained fruits, pecans, coconut and marshmallows.
Add more fruit juice, if too thick.
Should be smooth and creamy with fruit.

title: carrots for company
directions: Cook carrots.
Melt butter, cheese and milk.
Gradually add flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and cut in half lengthwise.
Scrape inside. Cut 1/8-inch thick slices.
Put in colander and sprinkle with salt.
Mix.
Leave for 10 minutes, then rinse.
Put in bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drain and serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip. Mix well.
Layer pudding, sliced bananas and vanilla wafers. Repeat until all is used in a large bowl or casserole dish. Refrigerate until set.

title: casserole bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir yeast and water together. Add sugar, salt and shortening. Stir until dissolved. Add flour and beat 2 minutes with spoon.
Cover batter with greased wax paper.
Let rise in warm place until triple in bulk (35 to 40 minutes). Beat with spoon for 1/2 minute.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes. Sprinkle top with cheese before baking. Cool before slicing.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onions and chopped pepper until bacon is crisp and onions and pepper are tender.
Drain off all grease.
Add tomatoes and cracker crumbs; simmer for 20 minutes until mixture thickens.

title: connie's chili
directions: Fry ground beef with onions.
Sprinkle one pack of chili seasoning in ground beef.
Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot (ground beef last).
Cook 3 hours.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and water for 5 minutes.
Add butter and garlic salt.
Make White Sauce.

title: chocolate chip cookies from cake mix
directions: Blend cake mix with oil and eggs until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top of cookies will be light in color.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: party wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream together butter and cheese.
Add salt, pepper and flour; mix well. Add nuts. Make into a large roll and wrap in wax paper. Chill overnight. Slice thin until light brown. Keeps well in tins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 2 cups crackers and oleo together and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then mix sour cream, soup and chicken and spread on top of the crackers.

title: mary's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and flavoring.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Stir all together alternating with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli approximately 4 minutes, then place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the Cheddar cheese over broccoli.
Blend mushroom soup and evaporated milk and pour over cheese and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with onion rings and return to oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix baking soda and boiling water and pour over raisins; let stand overnight.
Do not stir in the morning.
Add remaining ingredients to raisin mixture; mix well.
Grease and flour three 1-pound coffee cans and divide mixture evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 1/2 hour in cans before removing breads. Place cans on side and turn until bread is loosened.
Slice and serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: fresh fruit salsa
directions: Halve pineapple lengthwise.
Remove and discard peel, leaves and core.
Cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Halve papaya lengthwise; remove and discard seeds.
Pare and cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Halve apple; remove and discard core and peel.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a medium bowl, combine fruit and remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate.

title: banana cream layered pie
directions: Mix and pat into bottom of dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate one hour.

title: tropical banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Top with a pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
tags: Duncan Hines banana supreme cake mix

title: exquisite pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Make sure to mix well. Put in a greased pan and spread ketchup over the top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peach praline shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease round layer pan.
Measure flour, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl.
Cut in mixture 1/2 cup brown sugar and shortening until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in pecans.
Combine egg and milk.
Blend into flour mixture.
Put into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Split cake while warm.
Fill and top with peaches.
Blend sour cream and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Serve with shortcake.

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir lemon rind, vanilla and yogurt into batter. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana bread
directions: Melt margarine and add rest of ingredients, adding flour last. Mix together. Bake in 325° oven approximately 1 hour in prepared loaf pan.

title: mustard glazed ribs
directions: Mix together prepared and dry mustard.
Whisk in remaining ingredients.
Simmer over moderate heat for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cut ribs in strips and place in a baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Baste with glaze and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Turn and baste every 10 minutes.

title: five-hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a heavy kettle or large baking dish (no need to brown meat).
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°. Stir once during baking.
(If desired, cook in crock-pot instead for 12 to 14 hours on low setting.)

title: grapenuts cereal
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in medium oven; cool and dry, then grind.
Store in an airtight container until used. Serve cold.

title: shrimp salad(new orleans)
directions: Marinate all ingredients overnight in the Italian dressing. Next day, drain and use liquid for salads.
Serve on small bed of greens.
The longer this sits in refrigerator, the better it tastes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in the 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Combine onion mixture in a bowl with chopped chicken and green chili peppers; set aside.

title: perfect wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together very good except ginger ale. Divide punch into two containers (each container fills a punch bowl) and freeze overnight.

title: luscious potatoes
directions: Mix
all ingredients except cheese.
Put in baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bar cookies (chews)
directions: Mix in large bowl; pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not test for doneness with toothpick.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix together flour, powdered sugar and butter and pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Blend the remaining ingredients.
Put on the baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Brown chicken in skillet with oil.
Drain drippings reserving 1 tablespoon.
Saute onion, celery and garlic.
Stir in catsup, water, wine, bay leaf, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.

title: touchdown chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa. Cut in margarine.
Add egg. Save 1 1/2 cups of mixture.
Press remaining mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: all bran molasses muffins(no fat)
directions: Add cereal to molasses.
Add milk and allow to soak for 15 minutes.
Beat egg and add to first mixture.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Mix lightly.
Fill greased muffins pans 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12.

title: candied tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Slice tomatoes in half crosswise. Place the tomatoes on a baking sheet, cut side up. Pour olive oil over tomatoes. Sprinkle with salt as desired. Bake for 2 hours, until tomatoes are wrinkled on the outside, but somewhat moist in the center. Serve warm or cool. Store in olive oil in the refrigerator. Spoon them over chicken breasts for a main course. They are great on omelettes; sprinkle with fresh thyme or basil leaves. Use in sandwiches, whatever. They are delicious!

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil for ten minutes.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Bone and flake salmon.
Set aside the liquid and salmon.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the first 7 ingredients. Add cucumbers and onion; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.

title: brunch punch(servings:  50)
directions: Combine 8 cups water and 2 cups sugar in large boiler.
Boil for ten minutes, then let cool.
Puree bananas in blender.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, water, lemon juice and bananas to the sugar syrup.
Mix thoroughly and freeze in thoroughly washed 1/2 gallon milk cartons.
Add ginger ale at serving time.
Should be slushy when served.
Three minutes in the microwave creates the slush.
Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all listed ingredients.
Chill and serve.
May be placed in dessert dishes or in lettuce cups.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey-glazed chicken
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first 7 ingredients. Add chicken; seal and turn to coat. Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours. Place chicken and marinade in 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until juices run clear. Drain marinade and serve with chicken. Yield: 8 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Place carrots, celery and onions in a steamer and cook until tender.
In a large mixing bowl place steamed vegetables, bean sprouts, garlic and ginger.
Mix well, then add soy sauce and meat of your choice or all of the ingredients.
Put about 1/4 to 1/2 cup of mixture per wrapper.
Fold edges to center, then roll tightly. Spray pan with nonstick spray, then spray over top of egg roll. Bake in a 450° oven, turning once when brown, browning each side.

title: two minute microwave fudge
directions: In medium-size microwave bowl melt butter or margarine.
Mix sugar and cocoa together; add remaining ingredients.
Add to melted butter or margarine.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Stir. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In a small bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Chill until ready to use.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's pancakes
directions: In large bowl mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk in a separate bowl.
Add to first mixture, add oil and stir.
Pour on preheated griddle (about 4 on dial).

title: oyster stew
directions: Wash oysters thoroughly, and add to milk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook until well done.
Serve with crackers.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Combine all together and place on very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake to a light brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Place all ingredients, except brown sugar, in mixing bowl. Beat 2 minutes by hand.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle the brown sugar on top.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until done, at 350°.

title: summer salad surprise
directions: Chill Veg-All thoroughly.
Prepare Creamettes according to package directions for salad use.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, Veg-All, bacon and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Add mayonnaise, 1/2 of the parsley and seasoned salt.
Toss gently.
Serve immediately or chill 1 to 2 hours.
Just before serving, garnish with remaining onions and parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal pie(3 pies)
directions: Mix together and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, onions and green pepper in oil. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, 1 hour.
Uncover and cook minute.

title: nana's irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients. With a fork, mix in egg and butter.
Add raisins, stir well.
Add buttermilk, a little at a time, just enough to make the batter very thick; it should be very hard to stir.
Spoon it into a well-greased cast-iron skillet, sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Turn out of pan immediately, let bread cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook, debone and cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Cook noodles in the broth the chicken was cooked in, adding water, if necessary.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onions, green pepper and celery in margarine. Add milk, mushroom soup and mushrooms. Add cheese and mix well. Add noodles and chicken.
Pour into casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: leaf lettuce salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients but onions in small saucepan; cook on low until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add onions just before pouring on lettuce.
This dressing should be made just before serving or it tends to wilt lettuce.

title: coconut snow drops
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes. Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Cookies should still be white when done.)
Remove cookies from cookie sheets. Cool on wire racks.
Dust with powdered sugar. Store in airtight containers.
Yields about 4 dozen.
Pecan or cherry for center is optional.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve as main dish for luncheon or side dish with another meat.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Combine with onions, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Beat egg slightly and mix with sugar and milk.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, melted margarine and 1 egg. Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat 2 eggs, then add confectioners sugar and softened cream cheese. Spread over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: chocolate-amaretto pie
directions: Prepare topping mix according to package directions.
Add milk, pudding mix and Amaretto.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed of electric mixer.
Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Top with whipped topping and chocolate shavings, if desired.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: liverwurst and red onion on rye
directions: Spread small amount of mayonnaise on each slice of rye bread. Add liverwurst slices and red onion between bread.
Very good with a mug of cold beer.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Mix/cream first 4 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Drop by heaping tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Preheat
oven
to
In large bowl, stir flour, 1/2 cup sugar
and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, oil and vanilla; stir until
smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa;
gradually stir
in boiling water.
Pour liquid mixture over the batter in the pan. Bake
at
for 30 minutes or until test done. Serve warm or chilled.

title: marie's pecan pie
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cream.
Beat eggs and add to creamed ingredients.
Add Karo, salt and nuts.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, on "bottom rack of oven".

title: candy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter, shortening, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: oven roasted potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes, leaving skins on.
Cut lengthwise 6 to 8 wedges.
In small bowl, combine oil, salt, pepper and paprika. Toss potato wedges into seasoned oil.
Place wedges on foil lined pan and bake about 35 minutes in 450° oven.
Turn once while baking.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: Crush berries.
Add 2 cups water and lemon peel.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain through cheesecloth or jelly bag.
Squeeze to extract juice and pulp from berries.
Mix sugar and 4 cups water. Boil to 260°.
Add berry juice to sugar syrup.
Boil 1 minute. Add lemon juice.
Pour hot into hot jars.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken between pieces of waxed paper real thin.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take margarine, parsley and garlic and spread thin into a dish and freeze.
When frozen, remove and cut into 6 cubes.
Place 1 cube in each breast half with 1 slice Swiss cheese.
Fold 2 short sides, then roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Beat eggs with water and oil.
Roll chicken cylinder into beaten eggs, then roll in bread crumbs.
Chill thoroughly. (Can be prepared the night before.)
Fry in deep fat.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine soups, water, mushrooms and butter in pan.
Heat until butter has melted.
Then add rice to soup and mix well.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour soup over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done, uncovered.
Do not add salt.

title: chicken old ladies on a bus
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Combine marmalade, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Place chicken in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Increase heat to 400° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add bananas.
Add flour, baking powder and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in 350° oven in sheet or layers, 9-inch pan, 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft ball.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla; do not beat.
Stir and pour in pan or dish.
Let cool; cut into pieces.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple (do not drain) into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Dump in cake mix (dry).
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over mix. Slice margarine into pats and place evenly over other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top will be crunchy and firm when cake is done.

title: pecan roll
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil until crystals disappear.
Boil to 265° on candy thermometer.
Add the syrup to the beaten egg whites with the vanilla.
Shape into rolls and refrigerate.
Cook, stirring until thick, the Eagle Brand milk, salt and 1/2 cup corn syrup.
Cover cold rolls with sauce.
Roll immediately in chopped pecans.
Keep refrigerated.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices to serve.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts in order listed over butter and graham cracker crumb mixture.
Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until top begins to lightly brown.
Allow to cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Chill for several hours. Makes 1.5 cups.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix fruit and pudding.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar by tablespoons, then add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Oven must be preheated to 350° before beginning.
Drop by spoonfuls onto 1 cookie sheet. All the dough must fit on 1 sheet, so drop close together.
Place in oven for about 3 to 4 hours.
Cookies can not touch each other on the cookie sheet.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all together for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: portofina salad
directions: Add water to Jell-O in largest mixing bowl.
Stir in entire contents, cranberries and pineapple until well mixed.
Add nuts. Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until set.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip.
Spread on baked pretzel crust, sealing sides well. Refrigerate.

title: pepsi pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan.
Mix catsup and Pepsi; pour over top of pork chops.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: kissel
directions: Place raspberries and strawberries into a blender and whirl until smooth.
Pour mixture into a large saucepan.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and stir into fruit puree.
Stir over low heat until fruit bubbles and thickens.
Cool and then chill.
Serve very cold in small bowls topped with drizzles of heavy cream.

title: all-bran griddle cakes
directions: In a small bowl, stir together All-Bran and hot water.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat egg substitute and 1/2 cup skim milk. Add reserved All-Bran mixture, remaining milk and next 5 ingredients; stir until well combined.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Place shredded lettuce in bottom of pan.
Add layers of all or some
of the vegetables listed.
Add Mozzarella.
Make mixture of Parmesan, sugar and mayonnaise.	Cover salad.
Add Bac*Os or bacon
just before serving.
Let this set overnight if possible. The secret to having this salad really crisp and good is
getting all the moisture out of everything including the lettuce.
Blot it	with
a
towel	or
paper towels after shredding.
Be
sure other
vegetables
are squeezed out real dry.

title: chicken or turkey a la king
directions: Melt butter or oleo in top of double boiler over direct heat. Blend in flour; add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over boiling water until mixture thickens.
Stir to keep smooth. Add next 3 ingredients, cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add olives. Serve at once over toast, biscuits, Chinese noodles or in patty shells.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pretzel and fruit dessert
directions: Bake 6 minutes at 350° in oblong baking dish.
Cool.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix the oil, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over onion, green pepper, celery and kraut.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Add chips just before serving.
Can be made night before and add chips just before you are ready to serve salad.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter or margarine to softness. Mix all other ingredients together and bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat egg with a fork; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add cold milk
and stir until mixed.
Pour into large baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg and place in oven at 350° until thick and top browns.

title: parmesan american fries
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine cheese and salt.
Brush potato wedges with margarine; place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle wedges with cheese mixture to coat.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: country-style chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Meanwhile, on piece of wax paper, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Put all ingredients (except cheese and noodles) in slow cooker.
Stir; cover and cook 7 hours.
Put noodles in pan and pour chicken mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese; dot with butter.
Brown lightly in oven.

title: chocolate spread
directions: Melt the butter in a small saucepan.
Add the cocoa and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes over low heat.
Remove from the heat and leave to cool for 5 minutes.
Stir the cheese into the cocoa, then mix in the artificial sweetener to taste.
Chill the chocolate spread in a covered container and it will keep for about 3 to 5 days in the refrigerator, depending on the shelf life of the cheese.

title: zucchini french fries
directions: Combine eggs and water; beat well.
Add flour and beat until smooth.
Dip zucchini in batter and deep fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with salt. Serve immediately.

title: ham and cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender until ham is minced.
Roll into ball, chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: italian soup stew
directions: Combine tomatoes, sausage, tomato sauce, stock, onion, garlic, carrots, basil and oregano in large pot and simmer 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer an additional hour, adding more water as necessary to cook tortellini.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries, saving the juice from each. Heat juice and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Cool thoroughly (very important).
Add pineapple, nuts, cherries and Coke.
Pour into dish and chill until firm.

title: cocoa-nut layer cake(2nd place in pa state greatest cocoa cake contest)
directions: In a small bowl, mix cocoa with boiling water; cool completely.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch layer cake pans.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at high speed until fluffy.
At low speed, blend in flour mixtures (in fourths), alternately with buttermilk.
Begin and end with flour mixture; beat just until smooth.
Measure 1 2/3 cups batter into a small bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared pan.
Add cocoa mixture to remaining batter; mix until smooth and divide evenly between other pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack; remove from pans and cool completely.
Whip heavy cream until stiff.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate, remove from heat and stir in cream until smooth; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat egg; add sugar, milk, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate mixture; add bread and toss.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into greased 2-cup souffle dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with confectioners sugar or whipped cream.
Makes 2 servings.

title: strawberry pliatsok(shortcake)
directions: Wash, hull and slice strawberries.
Let drain; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Slowly add sugar; beat about 10 minutes.
Add baking powder to flour.
Add flour mixture slowly to egg yolk mixture.
Add vanilla; beat well until smooth.
Grease and flour an 11 x 15 x 2-inch cake pan or a jelly roll pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold batter into egg whites with wooden spoon gently.
Immediately pour into greased and floured pan and gently spread with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool. Mix strawberry glaze with strawberries.
Spread over cooled cake. Spread Cool Whip over all.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: yellow rice and corn casserole
directions: Cook rice; add margarine.
Add corn and soups and mix well. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit ice
directions: In a 2 cup measure, stir sugar into warm water.
Put all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan; cover and freeze 4 to 5 hours.
Transfer to large chilled bowl. Beat with mixer on medium for 2 minutes or until fluffy.
Return mixture to loaf pan; cover and freeze for 6 hours or until firm. Let stand 20 minutes at room temperature before serving.

title: sweet and sour sausages
directions: Brown sausages; drain on paper towels.
Boil together briefly vinegar, sugar, sherry, soy sauce and ginger.
Blend cornstarch and water and add to mixture.
Cook until transparent.
Add sausages, pineapple, green pepper and cherries.
Slowly heat.
May be made 2 or 3 days ahead of serving.
Serve in a chafing dish. Serves 6.

title: lancashire hot pot
directions: Trim fat from chops and roll in flour.
Place layer of chops, then onions, carrots and potatoes in large casserole, seasoning each layer lightly with salt and pepper.
Finish with potatoes. Pour stock over.
Cover.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Will also need a colander.

title: tuna pompons(low calorie)
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until soft but not brown. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and bouillon.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and thickened. Chill.
Mix sauce with rice, tuna and cheese.
Adjust seasoning, if necessary.
Form into 8 balls (1/3 cup each).
Roll in combined bread crumbs and paprika.
Place in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sauce made by combining and heating soup and sour cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
sweet potatoes,
eggs,
sugar
and
salt.
Mix well. Add soda, baking
powder,
vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 to 3 pies, depending on size and depth of pie pans.

title: flagstone fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Cut into bite-size chunks.
Whip cranberry sauce and add to fruit.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in a little oil, then add chopped onions.
Let brown.
Combine tomato sauce and tomato paste with 2 quarts of water.
Add hot pepper and salt.
Let cook for 3 or 4 hours on simmer.

title: 2 chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, chocolate and flour in a bowl.
Beat egg yolks. Add milk and vanilla.
Pour this in sugar, chocolate and flour. Mix well.
Add margarine.
Cook slowly until thick.
Pour in cooked pie shells.
Top with beaten egg whites.
Then brown in oven.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients; mix well and serve. Yield: 2 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Put pork and beans in a bowl; add cut up onions, brown sugar, mustard and chili powder.
Stir and then add bacon slices on top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, until bubbly.

title: sirloin steak
directions: Trim excess fat and gristle from steaks. Season generously with salt, pepper and a splash of olive oil. On a grill that is clean and hot, but not flaming, grill steaks to desired doneness (medium-rare is best).

title: apple cake
directions: Combine in a separate bowl peeled and sliced apples, walnuts, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In another bowl mix eggs, sugar and oil. Add flour, baking powder, salt, soda and vanilla, stirring well. Add apple mixture and blend together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Season pork steaks.
Dip in beaten eggs and then in bread crumbs.
Brown on both sides in hot oil for a few minutes, then turn down heat and let finish frying slowly until meat is tender. Don't cover.
Serve with potatoes, salad or any kind of vegetable. Serves 4.

title: deer steak
directions: Put grease in frying pan.
Flour, pepper and salt meat. Brown in grease.
Pour grease off and add 1 can mushroom soup, onion, garlic and 2 cans of water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to slow and simmer until thick and done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate overnight.
Add tomatoes just before you serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix
together
the
flour, butter and nuts.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Beat the
cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Add the large container
of whipped topping; spread over crust.
Mix pudding and
milk	until thick.
Spread chocolate mixture over cheese mixture.
Top	with small
container
whipped topping.	Cover with toasted coconut. Refrigerate.
Keeps for 7 to 10 days if refrigerated.

title: sausage ratatouille
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet over medium heat until brown. Stir to crumble; drain and set aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and pepper; saute 2 minutes.
Add eggplant and saute 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add squash and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add sausage and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or longer.
Add spaghetti sauce as desired.

title: sue's chocolate clairs
directions: Mix pudding, cold milk and Cool Whip until well blended and it starts to thicken (a few minutes).
In large glass baking dish (2 x 9 x 13-inches), put down a layer of the graham crackers. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture on crackers.
Add another layer of crackers on top.
Spread the remaining 1/2 of pudding mixture on crackers and top with another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate at least one hour (overnight is great).

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Mix milk and
eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Dip potatoes in liquid,
then
in flour.
Repeat process.
Place on greased baking sheet
and
drizzle butter over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: In a heavy 6-quart saucepan brown stew beef.
When brown, place potatoes, celery, onion, salt, carrot and water in.
Bring to a boil (keep saucepan partially covered); turn heat down to low and simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Season with pepper and add additional salt, if necessary.

title: baked beans in microwave
directions: Power Level:
High (100%), Medium (50%).
Total cooking time is 24 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Put on topping.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Spread rolls out.
Spread sausage on top.
Add cheese.
Roll from shortest end and chill.
Slice and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serves 32.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a saucepan, bring milk to a boil.
Stir in rice and raisins.
Cover; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes, or until most of the milk is absorbed.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Spoon into dishes; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: peach puff cobbler
directions: Drain peaches.
Heat 1/2 cup peach syrup, lemon juice and brown sugar to boiling.
Add peaches and remove from heat.

title: scallop and fish casserole
directions: Cook scallops and fish (haddock) for 5 minutes in salted, boiling water; drain.
Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour shrimp soup over fish and top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour in casserole; top with bacon pieces. Bake in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
When done, add oleo and stir until melted.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple and bring to a boil.
Simmer 2 minutes; set aside and let cool completely.
Whip cream.
Fold whipped cream and cottage cheese into jello mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper in skillet.
Drain and place in large casserole dish.
Place 3/4 bag of Tater Tots on top of hamburger.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of Tater Tots.
Set aside.
Add soup and milk in saucepan.
Cook until smooth.
Pour on top of hamburger, cheese and Tater Tots.
Sprinkle more grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange date-nut bread
directions: Sprinkle soda over chopped dates.
Add boiling water.
Drop in butter.
Mix and add sugar, egg, flour, nuts and orange zest. Mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350 oven for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes in food processor.
Add cheese and mayonnaise. Pour into serving dish and bake in oven until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry upside down pudding
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately to butter/sugar mixture; mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine cherry juice and sugar in pan and heat until sugar dissolves; add cherries.
Spread this over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Very good!

title: june's pull apart(breakfast roll)
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Slice and cut into small pieces the loaf of bread.
(I usually cut each slice into 6 small pieces.) Put half of the bread pieces evenly into bottom of pan.
Mix the following 5 ingredients together as for pie dough.
Sprinkle half of this mixture over frozen pieces; place the balance of the bread in pan and sprinkle the balance of the mixture on top.
Cover; let set overnight and bake in the morning in a 350° oven approximately 30 minutes.
Thaw frozen bread slightly to cut.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in skillet (or large microwave casserole) and cook green pepper.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk, mushrooms, soups, Cheddar cheese, chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with a bit of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Coat with garlic dressing and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Stir together all ingredients in large bowl.
Add chopped fresh cilantro if desired.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together, first dissolving the jello into the boiling water, then adding the fruit juice, thawed strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Add the nuts.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Place in refrigerator.
Keep the other half at room temperature.
When first half is firm, spread with 1/2 pint sour cream, then top with rest of gelatin mixture.
Place back into refrigerator.
Make this a day before you plan on serving.
This makes 9 medium size squares.

title: "painting" girl's casserole(must do night before)
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in a greased or sprayed 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika; cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cover and bake 1 hour or until set in center.
(Sit back with a glass of wine and spend time painting.)
Serve with tossed salad and bread or rolls.
Serves 6 to 8.
Easily halved for small families.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In large pan, brown meat in margarine.
Add onion, garlic, carrots, celery and green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, salt and black pepper.
Simmer on low for 35 minutes.
Add hominy or corn.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Yields 4 quarts.
May be refrigerated several days or frozen.

title: homemade orange sherbet
directions: Mix together well and place in ice cream bucket.
Crank until frozen!

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients; pour into mold and refrigerate until mixture is set.
Turn onto bed of lettuce; garnish with parsley.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well. Add milk and vanilla wafers, then add coconut and chopped pecans. Bake in tube pan at 250° to 255° for 1 1/2 hours or until dry looking on top.

title: shrimp pilau
directions: Clean, devein and boil shrimp.
Fry bacon.
Remove from skillet.
In the remaining bacon grease, fry onions over low flame until transparent.
Add tomatoes and cook for a few minutes.
Add seasonings, rice, shrimp and crumbled bacon.
Put into 1-quart casserole and cover.
Set oven at 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes. Stir with fork 2 or 3 times.

title: batter-fried shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails on.
Split shrimp part way through, butterfly fashion.
Combine flour, water, egg, sugar and salt to make a batter.
Dip shrimp into batter and fry in deep, hot peanut oil.
Fry until golden brown and drain on paper towels.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Stir in crabmeat, Swiss cheese and onions.
Pour into a pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh raspberry pie
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water; add jello and stir until dissolved.
Mix cornstarch in cold water until smooth and then add to jello mixture.
Cook until clear.
Fill pie shell with berries and pour mixture over them.
Cool several hours.
Serve with whipped topping.
Frozen berries can be used but decrease water or add a little more cornstarch.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pie crust (b)
directions: Cut ingredients with pastry blender.
Add water and mix.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer and refrigerate overnight.
Mix together salad dressing, seasoning and sauce.
Chill overnight.
Mix all salad with dressing just before serving.
Top with crushed Doritos.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Mix well; add peanut butter. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: st. jo hash brown potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix margarine, sour cream, soup and onion. Add to hash browns.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with cheese and fried onions.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple and add water to make 1 cup.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve lemon jello in the syrup.
Blend 1/2 of the jello with cream cheese.
When smooth, pour into pie shell.
Chill until set.
Arrange pineapple chunks on top and spoon remaining jello over to glaze.
Chill.

title: baked custard
directions: Scald milk in glass measuring cup for 3 to 4 minutes on High or until tiny bubbles appear around the edges.
Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add milk.
Divide into 5 glass custard cups or coffee cups.
Place custard dishes in a circle on the outer edge, rotating if necessary.
Heat in microwave, uncovered, on Medium for 5 to 5 1/2 minutes or until custard just begins to boil.
Center will become firm during standing time. Chill several hours before serving.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Crush cookies in food processor.
Add melted butter.
Press into 9 inch pie pan and up sides.
Chill.
Melt marshmallows with milk.
Let cool thoroughly.
Add creme de menthe.
Whip cream and fold into milk mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Save some crumbs for garnish.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by rounded tablespoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven until done.
These get better with age when stored in a tight container.
Makes 22 dozen.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs well.
Add dry ingredients.
Make 2 balls.
Place in the refrigerator until needed.
Slice 1/8-inch thick and bake in slow oven.

title: one pot dinner
