directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Brown bacon and onion. Drain off fat.
Mix the beef, bacon and all remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jettie's fruit cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to fruit and nuts; mix well.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and extract.
Add fruit and nuts to egg mixture; mix well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool in pan before removing.
Let mellow a few days.
It is delicious.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, saute in 1 tablespoon butter, the onion, bell peppers and celery.
Add broth and soups.
Mix well.
Add chicken pieces and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese. The more the better. (I like to mix shredded cheese into my spaghetti mixture and also cover the top.)
Bake until hot and cheese is melted (325° oven).

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans in cold water. Fill 5-quart Dutch oven with more water and add all of the ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer. Cook slowly, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking, for 2 or 3 hours or until beans are very tender.
Remove 2 cups of the beans with slotted spoon and mash thoroughly. Return to pot and stir to thicken gravy. Adjust salt, pepper and water (if dry).
Serve over steamed rice.

title: rescue recipe for "soupy" jam
directions: Mix water and powder pectin in a saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add 4 cups jam or jelly (needing to be thickened) and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir well, then bring to full boil. Boil one minute more.
Remove from heat; skim and pour into jars. Seal.

title: hillbilly dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, egg and shortening thoroughly. Add 1/4 cup broth to make dough stiff.
Roll dough into 1/4-inch thickness and cut.
Add milk to broth.
Heat and add dumplings, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a rolling boil, then turn heat down to low.
Cook slowly until done.

title: old field's layered blueberry pie
directions: This pie adapts itself to being made with or without an orange liquor and the taste is wonderful either way.

title: hot deviled potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions.
Heat sour cream (do not boil).
Add mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt and sugar; stir to blend.
Mix into hot potatoes with onion.
Immediately turn into 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla; beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on cooling rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable and meat salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. When ready to serve put one can of shoestring potatoes over top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing mix and margarine. Put half of stuffing in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add chicken on top. In a separate bowl, combine cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups with broth. Pour soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nutty zucchini bread
directions: Beat oil with eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to oil mixture; mix thoroughly.
Stir in grated zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Turn in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Fix rice per directions (20 minutes).
Brown ground beef; add onion, garlic, oregano and seasoned salt.
Simmer until done.
Add Chili-O mix or 2 tablespoons of chili powder.
Add tomatoes and water.
Simmer until rice is done.
Add rice to ground beef. Blanch green peppers (1 per person).
Fill with ground beef mixture.
Top with cheese.

title: easy oyster cracker snack
directions: Put crackers in paper bag.
Pour oil and seasonings in bag; shake well several times.
Store in airtight container.
Serve after 24 hours.

title: easy chicken
directions: Cook broccoli in salty water;
arrange in a greased 9 x 12-inch
pan.
Arrange
chicken
on
top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over broccoli and chicken. Top with bread crumbs or potato chips.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for cake together.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. While cake is still warm from oven, poke holes in cake. Pour Juice mixture into the holes
Let cool. Ice and serve.

title: rice pudding louisiana style
directions: Combine and mix well first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole that has been greased with butter.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Top with butter for the last 15 minutes of cooking time.
Serve warm topped with heavy cream. Serves 6.

title: sweet-sour veal with rice
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
In skillet, brown veal on all sides in hot shortening.
Add onion, salt, pepper and reserved syrup.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water, pour over meat. Cover; simmer 50 minutes.
Add celery; cook until meat is tender, 10 minutes more.
Mix cornstarch with soy sauce and vinegar, stir into hot mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add pineapple and mushrooms.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: baked scallops
directions: Wash scallops and dry.
Put in a 8-inch pie plate.
Mix ingredients to make stuffing.
Put stuffing on top of scallops. Add a dab of margarine.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and pineapple.
Add flour.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: trustee turner's tacos
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Cut up lettuce and add diced tomato.
In very hot oil, drop tortilla, using 2 forks.
Turn tortilla over right away and fold in half.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towel.
Cook each tortilla individually.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, spices and plums well.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a tube pan.

title: quick and easy frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; beat gently with wire whip.
Spread immediately on your favorite cake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
A very light, fresh tasting frosting.

title: tortellini
directions: Saut onion and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Add next 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir in tortellini and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese. Yield:
4 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: In mixing bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, salt and water.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Saute bacon.
Add onion.
When cooked, drain fat.
Add all other ingredients to the beans.
Bake in casserole or crock-pot for 1 hour at 375°.

title: honey chicken
directions: Melt butter in foil-lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken in butter and sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Blend remaining salt, honey, mustard and lemon juice.
Brush 1/2 honey mixture on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; brush with remaining honey mixture.
Bake 20 minutes longer until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan cheese crackers
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Cream thoroughly.
Add pepper, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Shape into rolls.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: spaghetti style pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Beat milk and eggs together.
Toss with spaghetti.
Spread spaghetti mixture into greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with Ragu sauce. Crumble beef evenly over sauce.
Add pepperoni and mushrooms. Sprinkle on Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pork chop and potato scallop
directions: Mix together sour cream, cheese soup, water and parsley.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer sliced potatoes, sliced onions and several slices green pepper (2 large potatoes and 1 large onion for 4 pork chops).
Cover with soup mixture.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Form into a roll as for icebox cookies and roll in colored sugar.
Chill several hours.
Cut in slices and bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: corn puff curls
directions: Boil on low heat the vanilla, brown sugar, Karo and oleo for 15 minutes.
Place the corn puff curls in roaster.
Pour the syrup over the corn.
Stir with wooden spoon (doesn't break corn up). Bake in a 250° oven for
1 hour.
Keep mixture stirred. Corn should be coated and not sticky.
Bag when cool.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour and mix. Spoon into miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: citrus veggie stir-fry with cashews
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients until blended. Set aside. In a large nonstick skillet or wok, stir-fry carrots and peppers in oil for 5 minutes. Add mushrooms and snow peas; stir-fry for 6 minutes. Add green onions; stir-fry for 3 minutes or until the vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir orange juice mixture and add to pan. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in cashews. Serve with rice. Yield: 4 servings.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar and pudding.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in Cool Whip, nuts and vanilla.
Can use any instant pudding.

title: coconut balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls, using 1 heaping teaspoonful for each.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Combine remaining ingredients in top of double boiler.
Heat, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Keeping chocolate mixture over hot water, dip coconut balls until thoroughly coated.
Remove from chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until hardened.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: peach or apple crisp
directions: Put apples or peaches on bottom of greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg.
Add mixture to fruit.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie slaw
directions: Shred and combine the following ingredients: cabbage, carrots, celery, green peppers and onions.
Toss well. Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and garlic.
In a larger bowl combine both mixtures.
Chill for one hour and then it's ready to serve.

title: nacho turkey franks
directions: Grill franks 4 to 5 minutes.
To serve, place each frank on bun, drizzle with melted cheese and sprinkle with crushed chips. Top with jalapeno slices.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and cut into chunks. Mix crackers, margarine and poppy seeds; set aside. Mix soups and sour cream in a bowl; set aside. Cover bottom of 2-quart deep casserole dish with 1/2 cracker mixture. Place chicken on top; cover with soup mixture. Top with remaining cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl; chill before serving.

title: my mom's syrup pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour mixed together.
Add syrup, butter, water and vinegar; mix well.
Bake in 9-inch uncooked crust at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix with eggs and oleo.
Add your choice of chips or nuts or both.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
Cool.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.
Cool.
Serve with grilled fish or chicken.
Yield:
1/2 cup.

title: quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese and chopped onion in unbaked pie shell.
Beat eggs, then add light cream, salt and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into pie shells and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°; reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chili green beans
directions: Heat green beans with the chili sauce.
When ready to serve, remove to bowl with slotted spoon.

title: hamburger cabbage dish
directions: Brown beef in large pan and pour off drippings.
Add onion and tomatoes with juice.
Simmer until onions are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cabbage and simmer until cabbage is tender but not overcooked.
Serve this mixture over mashed potatoes.

title: angel party dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Soak gelatine in water.
Mix egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Cook to coat spoon.
Add gelatine and cool. When it begins to thicken add remaining ingredients.
Grease generously 2 angel food pans or long loaf pans.
Alternate chunks of cake and dessert mix.
Chill at least 24 hours.

title: spinach bread
directions: Allow dough to thaw.
Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain.
Remove sausage from casing and brown.
Roll dough in two large squares.
Beat egg, (reserving a little) and mix into spinach.
Spread half spinach, sausage and mozzarella cheese onto each loaf.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Fold edges of dough and roll up, sealing ends.
Brush tops with remaining egg and score tops slightly.
Allow to rise for 1-2 hours.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Serves 8.

title: gingerbread man
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Mix well. Divide dough into thirds.
Wrap each well.
Cool for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut out and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 200 gingerbread men.
It is best to use a 2-inch cookie cutter.

title: beef stock
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread beef bones in a baking pan just large enough to hold the meat in a single layer.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is very brown.
Turn the pieces occasionally and drain rendered fat as necessary.
Heat the oil in a large pot. Add the onions, leeks and carrots and cook over high heat, stirring often until well browned, about 25 minutes.
Add the browned bones to the vegetables, along with the remaining ingredients.
Pour 1 cup of water into the pan in which the meats were browned and set over high heat.
Stir and scrape up any caramelized particles from the bottom and sides.
Pour the liquid into the pot.
Add additional water to cover the ingredients well and set the pot over medium heat.
When the stock reaches a boil, skim.
Reduce heat. Partially cover and simmer for 4 hours.
Skim occasionally.
Strain out and discard the solids and refrigerate or chill, then freeze the stock.
Before using refrigerated stock or freezing chilled stock, remove any fat that has solidified on top.
Yields 2 to 3 quarts.

title: orange preserves
directions: Squeeze juice out.
Slice oranges and lemons into thin slices. Place the sliced fruit in a pot with 1 1/2 cups water.
For each cup of pulp, boil 30 minutes, then add the juice and 1 can of No. 2 pineapple.
Then add equal parts of sugar to juice and pulp.
Boil until jelly test or as thick as you desire it.
Cook slowly.
Pour into jars.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: This recipe was used by my grandmother, Luella McClintick Runyan, 1862-1937.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining cake mix, oil and 1 egg; beat until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In same bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over prepared crust.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until set.

title: boston brown bread
directions: In a saucepan cover raisins with water and bring to a boil. Set aside to cool.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: taco dip salad
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Top with cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Serve with taco chips.

title: hot wing dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Place in baking dish (13 x 9 pan or two 9-inch pie plates) and bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Dip nacho chips or crackers into warm dip and enjoy.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Mix milk, flour, sugar and vanilla flavoring together well. Pour peaches into pan or casserole dish.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Brown in oven at 350°.

title: broccoli-rice-cheese casserole
directions: Mix cooked rice, can of cream of mushroom or chicken soup, 4 ounces Cheddar cheese and cooked broccoli.
Pour into remaining dish; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: bammys strawberry cake
directions: Mix Jell-o in boiling water, let cool slightly.
In a large mixing bowl combine cake mix with oil.
Mix, add eggs one at a time.
Add Jell-o and fold in one cup of strawberries.
Pour batter into 3 8 or 9 inch round cake pans.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cake cool.
Beat Dream Whip by pkg. directions, fold in remaining strawberries.
Spread mixture between layers, on sides and on top.	Keep in refrigerator!
Enjoy!

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt the almond bark.
Fold in the following ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Place in container and store in refrigerator.
Keeps a long time.

title: fried clams
directions: Mix together well. Dip clams in batter; fry in hot deep fat until golden brown. Drain.

title: citrus rice pilaf(makes 4 servings)
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook rice and onion in margarine until lightly browned, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth and steak sauce; heat to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in almonds, orange pieces and parsley; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: jellied beet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add rest of ingredients, except beets.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in beets and pour into mold; chill.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 2 cups hot water; using juice from pineapple, add water to make 2 more cups. Chill until slightly thick. Whip. Add pineapple and softened Philadelphia Cream Cheese. Mix thoroughly. Fold with whipped Jello mixture and refrigerate overnight in a rectangular dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water, then dissolve over hot water.
When gelatine is melted, add all remaining ingredients. Pour into mold.
Chill until set.

title: refrigerator pickles(canning)
directions: To make brine, boil water, vinegar, sugar and salt; cool.
In a gallon jug (or 4 quart jars), put hearts of garlic, dill and spices.
Slice cucumbers lengthwise and fill jug or jars.
Pour brine into jug or jars; let stand for 24 hours.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy cucumbers
directions: In a bowl, combine the first four ingredients; season with salt and pepper.
Stir in cucumbers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick supper
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add seasoning.
Drain excess fat and add tomatoes, mushroom soup, tomato paste and instant rice.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: takuwan
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat until sugar and salt dissolve.
Cool slightly; slice turnips and put in jar.
Add hot liquid and pepper.
Let stand at room temperature 1 to 2 days (taste).

title: red, white, blue cake(blueberry pie)
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 inch dish.
Spread cherry pie filling over bottom.
Spread the blueberries evenly over the cherries. Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the blueberries.
Drizzle the melted butter over the top.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix
vinegar,
cooking oil and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Mix all
other	ingredients.
Pour vinegar mixture over kraut mixture. Store tightly covered overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken pie
directions: In a greased pan, put chicken meat.
Cut eggs and put on top of chicken.
Mix soup and broth and pour on top.
Mix flour, milk and margarine real good and drop by spoon until thin crust covers top. Bake in oven at 425° until brown and bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: egg-sausage quiche
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: marinated grilled chicken breasts
directions: Make marinade with soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Put chicken in marinade at least 3 hours.
(It is better for 8 to 12 hours, covered, in refrigerator.)
Remove from marinade and cook on grill for 10 to 15 minutes per side.

title: rice pudding (rooz ib haleeb)
directions: Rinse rice, drain and place in a pan.
Add water, cover and simmer over medium heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
As it begins to thicken, add sugar and rosewater or vanilla.
Continue stirring until the rice is soft or well done. (This should be like a cream filling.)
Remove from heat and pour directly into dessert dishes to cool, serves 6 people.

title: susan's sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill for 4 hours.
Shape into balls.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix the cheese, flour, pepper and salt.
Set aside.
Cut potatoes in eighths lengthwise; rinse and leave wet.
Coat potatoes in cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Drizzle with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Top with parsley; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.
Remove foil and let brown.

title: black bean soup
directions: Before washing beans, spread on flat surface and pick broken beans out.
Look for foreign particles such as tiny little stones. Wash beans well and soak overnight in 2 quarts of water.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables well.
Add chopped vegetables.
Mix salt, pepper, olive oil, sugar, wine vinegar and water.
Mix well.
Pour marinade over vegetable mixture and marinate for at least 12 hours.
Will keep in fridge up to 2 weeks.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, adding onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir in seasonings, sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Break half spaghetti (raw) into lightly greased casserole.
Cover with half the sauce and half the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: baked dropped pudding
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and set aside.
In 9 x 13-inch pan mix remaining ingredients well.
Drop reserved mixture into the sauce by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Mix together until warm.
Pour over cakes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice with salt according to instructions.
Saute onion, peas and carrots in margarine on high heat.
Add cooked rice and fry, while stirring, until mixture starts to brown.
Sprinkle with sesame oil.
When rice begins to separate, add soy sauce to taste. Serve topped with a mixture of cubed zucchini, coarsely chopped onions and mushrooms (optional), which has been fried separately in a little oil.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate coconut crunch cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
In a small bowl, whisk together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In a medium bowl, with an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in the eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix on low speed until blended.
Add the flour mixture; mix just until blended.
Do not overmix.
Add the coconut, chocolate chips and almonds; stir until just incorporated.
Drop the dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes, or until set.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add other ingredients and heat to boiling.
Be careful not to burn to the bottom of the pan.
Serve with crackers or cooked macaroni.

title: cornbread dressing and pork chops
directions: 1st Step:
Crumble cooled cornbread.
Add enough broth to moisten.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls (unrolled) over pan; press edges together to seal.
Turn edges up.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle hash browns, veggies, salt and pepper on crust.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix well.
Pour over mixture. Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Over this sprinkle other ingredients, except Eagle Brand milk.
Pour Eagle Brand over all. Do not stir.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and then cut into squares.
Rich and delicious.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Line pan with lemon slices, capers, bay leaves, onion slices and shrimp.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Stir altogether and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pie deluxe
directions: Mix stuffing, bread crumbs and margarine thoroughly; reserve 3/4 cup of topping.
Pack bread mixture in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of bread mixture.
Add reserved crumbs on top.
Bake in hot oven (425°) until hot and bubbly with crumbs browned.
Set 10 minutes before cutting into 6 squares.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Pre-boil sweet potatoes for about 10 minutes.
Pour water out and cool potatoes with cold water.
Peel when cool enough.
Slice potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a 1 to 2-quart pot.
Bring to a boil.
Pour sugar mixture over potatoes.
Preheat oven to 300°. Bake for about 1 hour.

title: bostonian blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin tins.
Combine dry ingredients, except 1 tablespoon sugar in bowl and blend.
In separate bowl, toss 1 tablespoon dry ingredients with berries; set aside.
After butter has cooled slightly, stir in milk, then eggs and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and stir until well moistened.
Stir in berries.
Spoon into muffin tins. Sprinkle with reserved sugar.
Bake 15 minutes until golden brown. Let muffins stand 15 minutes before removing from tins.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Grease baking pan with some butter.
Heat 1/2 cup butter, 3 cups marshmallows, 1/2 cup dry milk and half of 1/2 cup milk.
Mix in saucepan over low heat until smooth, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in cereal and coconut until coated.
Empty into the buttered pan.
Rub a little butter on the back of the spoon and use it to pat the mixture evenly in the pan.
Cool. Cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.

title: dutch sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar. Add eggs and sour cream alternately with flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla and butter flavoring. Mix well. Mix brown sugar, cocoa, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle over mixed cake in tube pan (greased and floured). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together, may double recipe.

title: gorgonzola biscuits
directions: Using a stand mixer and paddle attachment, cream the butter. Add the cheese and
mix thoroughly. Add the flour, egg yolks, nutmeg and salt and pepper. Mix until dough just comes together and gently pat into a square. Wrap dough in plastic and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together as for pie dough; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 8 ingredients and then pour on dough.
Mix the remaining ingredients together, then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or longer until knife tests clean.

title: melt-in-your-mouth pineapple dessert
directions: Cream powdered sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Pour this mixture over vanilla wafers that have been spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan. Beat the whipping cream, fold in the drained pineapple.
Spoon over egg mixture.
Sprinkle with more crushed wafers and crushed pecans.
Refrigerate until served.

title: deep-dish pizza pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch glass pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Brown ground beef and onion in medium skillet over medium-high heat until beef is thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently.
Drain.
stir in 8 ounces pizza sauce until well mixed.
Carefully unroll dough in sprayed pie pan so edges extend over sides.
Pat dough in bottom and sides of pan, leaving dough extended over sides.
Spoon ground beef mixture into crust.
Top with half cheese, pepperoni and remaining cheese.
In small bowl, slightly beat egg and water.
Fold extended edges of dough up and over filling.
Seal all edges.
Brush crust with egg mixture. Bake 38 to 48 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat cider, spices and sugar to boiling.
Simmer 20 minutes and strain.
Keep warm in crock-pot until you finish it!

title: dennis' favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and eggs
well in bowl; mix well. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: sour cream cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Heat sour cream until warm; add yeast and rest of ingredients.
Stir in flour and let stand for 5 minutes.
Roll out and sprinkle dough with melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
May be frosted with thin powdered sugar icing.

title: apple raisin slaw
directions: Mix apple pieces and lemon juice in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage and boil in salted water until tender.
Saute vegetables in oleo.
Drain cabbage and add to vegetables.
Add creamer, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 5 minutes. Mix in bread crumbs.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cook for several hours, then add 3 slices cooked bacon, crumbled.
Add 2 tablespoons of bacon fat.

title: german coffee cake(dessert)
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and flavorings.
Add oil and water.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat for 8 minutes.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Mix nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of batter in pan, then half of cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Cover with remaining batter; top with remainder of cinnamon/sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta and drain. Cook hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Season with salt and pepper. Add pepperoni and mushrooms. Add Ragu sauce and heat through.
Mix pasta and hamburger sauce together; put in casserole dish. Top with grated cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Should be sloppy, not dry.)

title: meat dish
directions: Brown meat with onions and pepper.
Mix eggs, 1 cup corn and milk with corn bread mix.
Grease baking dish.
Pour corn bread mix on bottom of layer, meat and onions next.
Then remainder of corn and 4 slices of cheese on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in apples, nuts and extract.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain, with ice cream or with whipped cream.

title: pinto beans
directions: Cover with water and simmer until done.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Beat eggs. Add Ricotta cheese, spinach and salt. Grease 9 x 13 pan and cover bottom with sauce.
Layer noodles, cheeses and spinach mixture. Repeat layers. Cover with greased foil. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and cream of tartar, then sift again.
Cut in the butter. Add a handful of dried cranberries or raisins and the beaten eggs. Blend everything well and then begin adding buttermilk, a little at a time, until you have formed a stiff dough.
Roll the dough out on a flat surface to a thickness of 1 1/2-inches, then cut out 2-inch round.
Place on parchment paper and brush with beaten egg and bake for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix well in blender.
Pour over 1 head well chopped cabbage. Best if chilled 24 hours.
Extra sauce will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: orange cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. In a large bowl, combine cake mix and the cooking oil. Add eggs, one at a time, then the orange extract. Beat well. Add the pinch of salt and the dissolved gelatin. Beat 3 minutes. Turn into a greased and floured 10-inch angel food cake pan or Bundt pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crock pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in a large mouth jar and add the other ingredients.
Put weight on top of jar to keep the cucumbers in the brine (about 10 to 12 days), then store in refrigerator. They will keep about 6 months, if they last that long.

title: alice weeks' quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate drops in top of double boiler.
Add milk.
Mix well; does not need beating.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Line a dish with broken pieces of marshmallows.
Pour candy over and let stand in refrigerator about 3 hours.

title: cream cheese muffin puffs
directions: Flatten biscuits.
Put cheese in middle.
Fold over.
Roll biscuits in melted butter and vanilla first, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place seam side down on ungreased muffin pan.
Bake 12 to 18 minutes at 375°.

title: pork chops and peas
directions: Dip pork chops in seasoned flour; brown on both sides in oil. Top with black-eyed peas.
Add diced onion and garlic powder. Cover.
Simmer 1 hour or until pork chops are completely done and tender.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Add the flour.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 325°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add marshmallow cream.
Blend well.
Add Cool Whip.
Serve with chunks of cantaloupe, honeydew, pineapple, apple, banana, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: quick shortcake
directions: Melt butter.
Take biscuits and dip in the butter and then in sugar.
Put on baking pan and bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until brown.
Pour strawberries or other fruit over these.
This is delicious.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions, garlic and peppers into container. Sprinkle salt over ingredients.
Cover and let stand overnight or cover with cracked ice and let stand 3 hours; drain.

title: tom's salsa
directions: Blend in blender first 7 ingredients.
Blend in the tomatoes.

title: guyana rice treat
directions: Clean shrimp and remove shells.
Saute shrimp in oil for about 3 minutes or until pink.
Stir occasionally.
Add vegetables and continue cooking for 5 to 10 minutes or until vegies are crunchy. Stir occasionally.
Add cooked rice, pepper, salt and diced pineapple.
Mix well together.
Allow to become quite hot.
Spoon lightly into pineapple shell.
Garnish with parsley and serve hot.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients with sugar in bowl, mixing well. Blend in rest of ingredients. Shape into small balls; roll in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pork chops(for those on a salt free diet)
directions: Press cracker crumbs onto both sides of chops.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning once.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in shape of ball.
Refrigerate overnight and sprinkle with parsley.

title: wilmington island marsh mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease a 13 by 9 inch pan with butter. In a large mixing bowl, stir together the cocoa and the melted butter. Add the eggs, flour, granulated sugar, salt, and vanilla. Beat well with a hand held electric mixer. Add nuts, stirring with a rubber spatula. Pour batter into the prepared pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: When squash is done and cool, take inside out.
Mix with sour cream, a little salt, brown sugar, bread crumbs and cinnamon.
Mix together and then put back in shell.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until brown.

title: fish and potato cakes
directions: In small skillet over medium heat, heat the oil, then saute the onions, green onions and parsley until the onions are clear. Pour them into a large mixing bowl with the potatoes, fish, salt and hot sauce, then stir in the egg, garlic powder and bread crumbs.
Form into patties and fry in 1/4-inch of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, turning once until golden brown on both sides.
Yield:
10 to 12 (3-inch) patties.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients then add mandarin oranges (not drained) and stir.
Put in greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients to biscuit dough consistency.
May add flour if needed.
Roll out dough on floured surface; cut into strips about an inch wide.
Boil chicken; take chicken out of broth to cool.
Drop strips one at a time into boiling chicken broth; keep pushing down dumplings.
Boil for about 20 minutes. You may cut pieces of chicken and add to dumplings.

title: salad(korea)
directions: Chop eggs.
Thinly slice spinach; add next 3 ingredients. Toss lightly with French dressing.
One cup fresh bean sprouts, blanched in water and cooled may be substituted for canned bean sprouts.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sugar-free date coffee cake
directions: Beat banana and butter in mixer bowl until creamy. Add eggs, vanilla and water; beat until smooth. Add mixture of flour, baking soda and baking powder; beat until smooth. Stir in 1 1/2 cups dates. Spread evenly in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix coconut, walnuts and 1/3 cup chopped dates in small bowl. Sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. Yield: 10 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Wrap each breast in a strip of bacon and lay on chipped beef. Combine soup, cream cheese and sour cream to make a sauce; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours. Uncover for the last hour.

title: velvet lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add cream cheese; beat thoroughly and let thicken.
Add pineapple, whipped cream and nuts.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Heat all juices and dissolve jello.
Add other ingredients. Mix well and chill
until set.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and shortening.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture for on top of cake.
In another bowl, mix molasses and baking soda.
Add boiling water slowly, stirring.
Pour molasses mixture into flour mixture and stir.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Sprinkle reserved flour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: jello apple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add mayonnaise to milk. Stir into Jell-O.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: nutty fingers(candy)
directions: Cream sugar and butter and combine all ingredients to form a stiff dough.
Shape into hickory nut size balls.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and margarine in 2-quart saucepan on low heat.
Stir constantly until melted; remove.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: filled coffee cake
directions: Mix by hand the sugars, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs, flour and baking powder.
Pour half of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Spread with pie filling. Pour remaining batter over the top.
Sprinkle again with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy two-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar and milk.
Stir over medium heat until it forms soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Blend.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut when firm.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
blender
or
mixer and mix until smooth (sometimes it is thicker than other times).
Will keep in refrigerator several days.
Gets thicker in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups, equal to one 14 ounce size can.

title: one dish meal
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over rice and let stand while preparing the following: Brown hamburger, butter and onions. Remove from fire and stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix with rice and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vinegar.
Add seasoning packet and noodles.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: green pea and egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange on bed of lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers, then bananas, then pudding.
Repeat the layers again and top with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: herbed cream cheese
directions: Blend herbs into softened cream cheese using a food processor or electric mixer or by hand with fork.
Cover and chill.

title: herb bread
directions: Slice bread on angle all the way through.
Place 1 slice cheese between bread slices.
Mix other ingredients and spread over bread top and sides.
Roll in foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan per box instructions.

title: california salad
directions: Put garlic pieces on toothpicks.
Shake lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper, curry powder, mustard and garlic together in jar. Add avocado 1 hour before serving.
Wash, dry and refrigerate greens.
Break into pieces in bowl; toss with dressing.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can use any combinations of lettuce.

title: skillet braised pork chops italian style
directions: Cut fat from edge of a chop and rub it over the bottom of a skillet to grease it.
Discard fat.
Add chops and brown on both sides.
Add tomato sauce and oregano.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
During last 5 minutes, top each chop with a slice of cheese.

title: garden salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve in boiling water.
Add salt, lime juice, Sucaryl and food coloring to tint a light green. Chill until thickened.
Fold in balance
of ingredients.
Spoon into lightly oiled ring mold.
Chill until set.
Fill center with crisp fresh greens.

title: gingered carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans; set aside.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter; add sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and milk; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and mix well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls, roll in white sugar or colored sugar for holidays.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Hershey's Kiss on cookie until the cookie cracks slightly.

title: new york pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water, then stir in warm water and brown sugar.
Slowly add 5 cups flour, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring until mixture is smooth and doesn't stick to sides of bowl.
Dip hands in flour and knead dough until stretchy and smooth (5 to 10 minutes).
Grease cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sheet with salt from pretzels on separate surface, then fill frying pan with water (for each cup of water, add 1 tablespoon baking soda). Place pretzel in frying pan.
Count to 30 slowly; set pretzel onto salted cookie sheet and sprinkle salt on top.
Bake for 8 minutes at 475°.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together and let congeal.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg.
Cool and pour over first layer.
Whip cream cheese and whipping cream.
Top the other layers.
Sprinkle top with grated yellow cheese.
Chill.

title: almond-orange biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a baking sheet.
Shake off excess.
In a large bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Make a well in center of mixture.
To the well, add remaining ingredients.
With your hands, work dry mixture with liquid until a dough has been formed.
Divide the dough in half.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse and drain.
Melt about 1/4 stick butter and 1 tablespoon olive oil in frypan.
Sprinkle minced garlic. Use all of raw shrimp.
Saute shrimp in melted mixture until cooked.
Turn down to low fire.
Put in all of spaghetti.
Mix up well to heat spaghetti and make sure you have enough butter and olive oil to cover spaghetti in pan, cover for about 60 seconds, and ready to serve.

title: shrimp rolls
directions: Prepare marinade by combining sugar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, white wine and lemon juice.
Shell shrimps, leaving tails. Devein.
Wrap shrimps with 2 to 3 strips each of carrot and green onion in lumpia wrapper or egg roll.
Roll.
Seal with cornstarch paste.
Deep fat fry.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place all in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: special delivery chicken
directions: Combine sour cream and soup in a bowl; stir in chicken.
Pour into greased 11x7-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a baking dish, place the fruit.
Add remaining ingredients and
pour over the fruit.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans.
In large saucepan combine beans and 3 cups water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour (or soak by placing beans and 3 cups water in a bowl.
Cover and set in a cool place for 6 to 8 hours or overnight).
Drain beans in a colander and rinse.
Return beans to the saucepan.
Stir in onion, garlic, bay leaf, red pepper and 3 cups fresh water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Add ham chunks.
Cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Add water as necessary.
Stir occasionally.
Uncover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes more or until a thick gravy forms.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until white.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat after each.
Sift baking powder in flour.
Add milk, flavoring and flour alternately.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spanish tuna dip
directions: Cream butter until soft in a bowl; beat in flaked tuna, lemon juice
and	mayonnaise.
Fold
in olives; chill.
Spoon into small
dip	bowls.	Serve
with
crisp carrot and celery sticks or crackers.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll small cookies on the cookie sheet.
Then get glass of bottom, put sugars to press the cookies, then put them with cookie sheet in oven.
Great good cookies!

title: grand ridge potatoes
directions: Coat potatoes in flour, brown on both sides in hot oil.
Drain all the oil possible out of the potatoes.
Add milk to cover potatoes (13 ounce can Pet milk with cup of water makes better gravy).
Cover and cook on medium heat until potato is tender and gravy is thick.
Serves at least nine.

title: corn en casserole
directions: Place green pepper, onion and 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Cook gently until tender.
Add flour and seasonings; stir until smooth.
Add milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Crush 1 cup corn flakes; add with corn and egg to creamed mixture.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole (or 6 custard cups).
Melt remaining tablespoon of butter; pour over remaining 1 cup corn flakes.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle over top of corn.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes (20 minutes for custard cups).
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and salt. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add celery, crushed pineapple, diced apples and nuts to custard mixture.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Pour into container and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 1/2 hour before serving.
May be served on lettuce leaf.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix chicken and half of bread crumbs; set aside.
Melt butter on low.
Stir in 1/2 flour; cook slow.
Stir in milk, stirring slowly until you have a thick white sauce, about 1 1/2 minutes. Mix chicken and 1/2 of bread crumbs to white sauce.
Add chilies, green onion and garlic powder.
Make balls.
Roll in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep fryer at 350° until brown.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Put cake mix, lemon jello, water and eggs in a bowl; beat 3 minutes.
Add oil and beat 3 more minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chef salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and serve.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use Swedish Nut Cake Icing.

title: broccoli with carrots
directions: Place carrots in a steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover saucepan and steam 4 minutes.
Add broccoli and steam another 7 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste before serving.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: For best results, use homemade biscuits.

title: bunny's wonderful cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, ground nuts and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 4 hours.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Have butcher slice beef bacon-thin.
Put canned vegetables in deep saucepan.
Set heat on high.
Put in a layer of chopped vegetables, then a layer of meat.
Pull meat apart in thin strips, 2 x 3 inches or so.
Do not let burn.
Add soy sauce to keep from burning.
Reduce heat, but keep pretty high.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: Cook sausage and onion until brown; drain off excess fat.
Add rice, chicken bouillon cubes and hot water.
Heat to boiling. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add peas; cover and simmer for 10 more minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, applesauce, soda and water.
Add nuts and raisins with flour and spices.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: country corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking power, salt, corn with juice and sugar in a large bowl with 2 cups water until smooth.
Fold eggs in a separate bowl until well blended.
Add the flour mixture and mix until you have a pancake consistency.
Fry on medium high heat. Makes 16 to 24 fritters.
Serve with butter.

title: fluffy chiffon dessert
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Chill until partially set.
Using mixer, whip nonfat dry milk in gelatin until fluffy.
Serve immediately or allow it to reset in refrigerator. Contains 112 calories per serving.

title: crabmeat quiche(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Brush pie pastry with egg white.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes; let cool.
Mix crabmeat, parsley and vermouth.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter; cool.
Place marinated crabmeat, celery and onion in cooled shell.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
Strain over crabmeat and cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake about 10 more minutes, or until custard is just done in center.
Remove from oven.
Let cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: gooey butter cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pat into lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: In heavy pan, melt butter; add flour and mix until blended. Heat over low flame for 5 minutes, mixing occasionally.
Add chicken broth and half and half; mix until smooth and thick.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add beer and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in color and chives.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with popcorn.

title: caramel chess pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugars; add cornmeal and flour. Add milk, vanilla, melted butter and vinegar. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar.
Allow to cool; then beat in eggs. Add flour mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in chips.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit tray and dip
directions: Take Marshmallow Creme and mix well with Philadelphia cream cheese.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Mix and place in 9 x 13-inch pan in freezer.
Let soften before serving one hour before at room temperature.

title: tiffany's chili
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic and peppers. Add to rest of ingredients in a crock-pot. Cook for 4 hours. Add Franks red hot to taste.

title: angel food cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add all the other ingredients, mixing after each one.
Frost the cake.
Refrigerate.

title: crispy top pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and butter in a large mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl combine eggs, milk, vanilla flavoring and lemon juice (optional).
Sift plain flour and baking powder in a separate bowl.
Alternate adding small amounts of milk and egg mixture to sugar and butter with small amounts of flour with a medium speed mixer until completely mixed.
Add shortening and mix thoroughly.
Pour into preoiled and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple cream cheese refrigerated dessert
directions: Mix crushed crackers and margarine until crumbles. Put 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Chill large can of evaporated milk. Mix jello with scant cup of hot water and lemon juice. Allow to congeal slightly.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Combine butter and onion in 2-quart glass casserole. Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in tomato juice gradually.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Stir in milk gradually.
Microwave on Medium-high for 8 to 10 minutes or just to the simmering point, stirring every 2 minutes.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Garnish with croutons or oysters crackers.

title: eclairs
directions: Shape pastry into strips 1-inch wide and 4-inches long on baking sheet as for cream puffs.
When cool, split one side. Fill with Whipped Cream Topping* and frost with chocolate frosting. Makes 12 eclairs.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt butter in pan and mix with sugar, flour, and milk.
Drop sweetened peaches into mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans pieces.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: taco pasta
directions: Brown meat; add onions, pepper and taco seasoning in pan. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.	Place pasta in bottom of baking dish.
Place meat mixture on top, then top with sour cream and cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese melts.
Top with taco chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased 9 X 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy scambled eggs
directions: Variations:
Add 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese or ham.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix and add powdered sugar for proper consistency.
(This is edible.)

title: hot cheddar bean dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water. Stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add the lemonade concentrate, pineapple-grapefruit juice, water and orange juice concentrate.
Divide mixture in half. Freeze half of the juice mixture. Chill remaining half.

title: rich stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut in half; scoop out cooked potato from shells and combine potato with butter in bowl.
Add milk and mash lightly; stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill shells with mashed potatoes.
Top with cheeses and bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pickled bell pepper
directions: Pack peppers in jars.
Cover with boiling water.
Combine sugar, water and vinegar and boil.
Drain water from jars.
Put 1 teaspoon oil, 2 cloves of garlic and 1/2 teaspoon salt in each jar.
Pour hot syrup over peppers and seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Place bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Combine vanilla pudding and milk together.
Next, add sour cream and Cool Whip, blending thoroughly.
Line a Pyrex plate with vanilla wafers, cut up bananas and mixture.
Repeat with wafers, bananas and mixture until ingredients are gone.
Let chill 4 hours.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into graham cracker crust. Keep refrigerated.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and then add can of Ro-Tel and cooked, crumbled sausage. Stir together.
Serve hot or cold with chips. Delicious!

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Cook marinade for 10 minutes; cool and pour over steak. Marinate overnight or 10 to 12 hours.
Great for barbecue!

title: glazing for christmas pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and heat until sugar dissolves.

title: banana bread
directions: Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Nuts may be added.

title: mounds
directions: Melt
butter
or margarine and milk over very low heat. Stir continually.
Mix powdered sugar and coconut into mixture and place
on
cookie
sheet.
Place
in
refrigerator	until completely cold or overnight.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook and stir cornmeal and water until like mush.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baking powder, salt and butter.
Stir in milk and well beaten egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a greased 2-quart casserole in a slow oven at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all together. Spread on tray. Cover the top with 3/4 to 1 whole bottle of chili sauce.
Put into refrigerator and chill overnight.
Top with chopped crab as thick as desired.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, egg and onion.
Drop by heaping teaspoon into hot shortening.
Fry until golden brown.

title: crock-pot stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half and remove seeds. Combine all ingredients except peppers and cheese. Stuff peppers with ground beef mixture. Place in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours. Sprinkle with cheese during last 30 minutes of cooking time. Makes 6 servings.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Dip potatoes in oil.
Place in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika last 10 minutes of baking.

title: frosted lime-walnut salad
directions: Pour hot water over gelatin, stir until dissolved. Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese, celery and walnuts. Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Frost with combined cream cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: taco dip
directions: Chop olives, green onions (including tops), peppers (including seeds) and tomatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into walnut size balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325 for 20 minutes.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch loaf pan or casserole.
Mix all the ingredients all together and refrigerate 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roasted corn chowder
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Soak corn in cold water 30 minutes; drain.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Place sliced bacon on top.
Bake about 45 minutes at 400°.

title: michigan blueberry pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine berries and sugar.
Place over medium or low heat; stir
until berries cook into a sauce, about 15 minutes.

title: brittany's no bake cookies
directions: Mix well; drop
from spoon onto waxed paper or pour into pan and cut into squares when cooled.

title: the best brown rice
directions: Melt butter in a Pyrex dish.
Add rice and soups.
Stir together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Beat well.
Add beaten eggs, flour and milk.
Beat batter well; this is the secret to this cake. Stir in coconut.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: "apple" zucchini pie
directions: Cut zucchini into slices about size and shape of apple slices. (Remove large seeds.)
Mix ingredients.
Place in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with crust.
Bake at 375° until brown and bubbly.

title: quick and easy kolaches
directions: Lay out the biscuits like you're going to bake them.
Press out a hollow in the center of each biscuit.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together (more or less to taste).
Spoon into hollows of biscuits.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, spices, oats and raisins.
In a separate bowl, combine applesauce, oil, egg, vanilla, and sweetener.
Beat lightly and gradually add to dry ingredients.
Mix until lightly moistened.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375° or until lightly browned around edges.
I like to add chopped nuts when you add raisins.

title: chinese fish
directions: Brown chopped green peppers and garlic salt in oil.
Turn heat to 225°.
Add tomatoes and cook over low heat approximately 5 minutes.
Place fish (lightly seasoned with salt and pepper) into tomato mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. While fish is cooking, mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch with enough water to make a thin solution.
Add 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1/2 teaspoon Accent.
When fish is cooked, add mixture and glaze fish with it.
Layer chopped green onions, including the greens, over the fish and serve on a bed of rice.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add soy sauce, bouillon, soup, water and garlic.
Cook on low until meat is tender.
Add green pepper and cook until pepper is tender.
Add cornstarch (mix with about 1/2 cup water), stirring constantly while adding, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Serve on mashed potatoes with chow mein noodles sprinkled on top.

title: haddock italiano
directions: Cut fillets into serving size pieces.
In a shallow saucepan, melt margarine.
Add garlic.
Place bread crumbs in shallow baking dish or pan.
Dip fillets into garlic butter, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place fillets on baking sheet.
Drizzle any remaining garlic butter over fillets.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes per inch of thickness or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hay stacks
directions: Combine ingredients. Microwave 3 to 5 minutes. Drop on cookie sheet and put in refrigerator until set, about 10 minutes.

title: coffee glaze
directions: In a small saucepan, beat 2 tablespoons milk, 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and 1 teaspoon instant coffee until butter or margarine has melted.
Add to 1 1/2 cups confectioners sugar. Blend until smooth.

title: potluck bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 7 1/2 x 12 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for Pyrex dish).
In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter; pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Yields 24 to 36 bars.

title: raspberry apple jello
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil.
Stir into jello.
Add raspberries. Chill until firm.
May top with sour cream and nuts.
Yields 8 servings.
Preparation Time:
10 minutes.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Wash and drain artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients together; chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls; roll in Italian cheese.
Serve at room temperature.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix, milk, sugar, sour cream and half carton of Cool Whip.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers in large dish.
Add half of pudding mixture and add a layer of chopped bananas.
Repeat all three layers and spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Chill overnight.
Makes a light, cool dessert.

title: passion-orange chiffon pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup cold water in a saucepan.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add the 3/4 cup water.
Stir over low heat until the gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add passion-orange juice and blend.
Cool until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white and 3 ounces of whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Let set until firm.
Top with 1 ounce whipped topping.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: *Or 3 teaspoons cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon ginger and 1/2 teaspoon cloves.

title: flaky pastry(makes 2 double 9-inch pies and one 9-inch shell)
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture and blend with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
With hands, mold dough into a ball and chill at least 15 minutes. Dough can be stored in refrigerator for up to 3 days or it can be frozen until ready to use.

title: beet and meat soup
directions: In a stainless steel or enameled kettle, cover beef knuckles and marrow bones, chuck, beets and cold water.

Bring the water to a boil, skim the froth as it rises to the surface, and add celery, carrot, onion (all cut into 1-inch pieces), salt and bay leaf. Bring the water to a boil and simmer the mixture, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Do not dilute soups; spoon evenly over chicken.
Cover top with stuffing.
Melt margarine; pour over top.
Pour chicken broth over mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° (until brown).

title: tandy cakes
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and margarine. Set this aside.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
While hot, spread top with peanut butter.
Cool cake and pour melted chocolate over top.
Refrigerate until chocolate is set.
Cut into squares and store in a tightly covered container.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add flour and buttermilk to mixture.
Beat 5 minutes by hand.
Fold in jam, raisins and nuts.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make a syrup of the sugar, water and cinnamon.	Add the butter.
Sift the flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cut in the shortening.
Add the milk; stir until moistened.
Roll dough 1/4-inch
thick;
cut
into
5-inch squares.
Arrange 4 pieces
of apple
on each piece of dough; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Dot with butter.
Fold corners to center; pinch edges
together. Place,
inch
apart,
on a greased baking dish.	Pour
over the
mixture
of sugar, water, cinnamon and butter (which
has been brought to a boil).
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, or until apples are done.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Melt oleo in mashed
potatoes.	Beat in sugar, eggs and salt. Add flour, sifted with baking powder and nutmeg.
Dough should be just stiff	enough	to
handle without sticking.
If too stiff, add a bit of milk.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Beat all ingredients together except nuts.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Take out and roll in Saran Wrap to cover the nuts around cheese ball.
Twist at top and put in refrigerator to chill.
Serve with butter flavored crackers.

title: deviled island eggs
directions: Peel eggs; slice in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks and add mayonnaise; stir well.
Stir in salad dressing, relish, mustard and salt.
Stir in crumbled bacon. Spoon yolk mixture into egg whites.
Garnish halves with gherkin slices.

title: banana nut cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: special party punch
directions: Pour juice into punch bowl.
Add ice cream, using small spoonfuls.
Add ginger ale and stir slightly.
Serve immediately.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Combine milk and egg; stir well.
Combine flour and seasonings; stir well.
Dip each piece of chicken in flour; dip in milk and egg mixture and again in flour.
Fry in oil or Crisco until golden brown.
Reduce heat.
Cook, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with nonstick spray.
Place potatoes in the prepared dish.
Combine the salt, sour cream, pepper, onion and soup.
Pour over the potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Melt margarine and combine with corn flakes.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly and slightly brown around edges.

title: egg strata(can be prepared the night before.)
directions: In 9 x 13 baking dish, make a layer using half of the bread and then a layer using all of the meat.
Sprinkle on half the cheese and add another bread layer.
Sprinkle on the remaining cheese.
Dot with butter.

title: zesty tomatoes
directions: Cut a slice from top of each tomato; hollow out small well in center.
Season with salt and pepper and parsley.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture in well and on top of each tomato.
Broil 3 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and broil until lightly browned.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter with white sugar and eggs.
Add sifted flour, baking soda, salt, spices, coffee and vanilla.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Fix potato flakes according to package directions adding onion flakes to water.
Set aside to cool.
Add egg, cottage cheese and grated Cheddar, mixing well.
Put in well buttered casserole, top with Parmesan and garnish with chopped parsley.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes until set and lightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: pecan delight dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, margarine and 1/3 cup pecans. Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° until knife comes out clean. Bake 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Place cooked broccoli in casserole.
Blend undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with remaining ingredients in order.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook onion, carrots, pepper and peas in 1/4 cup cooking oil for about three minutes.
Add meat; remove from pan.
Add about 1/4 cup more oil and add rice.
Cover on low heat for about three to four minutes.
Add cooked vegetables to rice.
Scramble eggs and add to rice.
Season with soy sauce to your liking.

title: salsa
directions: Mix well in bowl; refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix poultry seasoning, cream of celery soup, chicken broth and cream of chicken soup together.
Layer in casserole dish: Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix, cubed chicken, soup mixture and end with stuffing mix.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Bake at 450° until thoroughly heated.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter long 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased pie plates. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: surprise cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with vegetable spray.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook until softened, stirring occasionally, 4 to 5 minutes.
Add zucchini.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup Monterey Jack cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup bread crumbs and the Italian seasoning.
Transfer the mixture to prepared dish. Sprinkle with remaining Monterey Jack cheese.
Combine beaten egg whites and half and half.
Pour over zucchini.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake until golden brown, about 35 minutes. This can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
Rewarm before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Add eggs, vanilla, butter and buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook 1 hour or until done.

title: mom's surprise
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cook	biscuits until they are light brown,
but
not
done.
Brown ground beef, drain well. Add onions; cook until tender.	Add barbecue sauce and beans. Heat until sauce bubbles.
Put into ovenproof dish.
Top with partly cooked
biscuits
and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until biscuits are brown (about 20 minutes).
Serves 4.
Serve with salad.

title: elda dodge's sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix and chill several hours.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all together and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: goulash soup - german style
directions: Cut roast into small pieces and cook slowly until done.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Add more seasonings until taste is to your liking.
Thicken soup with cornstarch until desired consistency.
Nothing is better on a cold winter evening!
Serve with warm, crusty bread.

title: bea's brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a pot.
Add sugar and cocoa; mix.
Add eggs and mix.
Add vanilla and flour.
Pour on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or so.
Quick and chewy.

title: lemon stickies
directions: Mix dry cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Dough will be stiff.
Press or spread in a well greased 8 1/2 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix together softened cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread over dough mixture and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
This freezes well.
Good served with Cool Whip and a cherry on top!

title: lemon pie squares
directions: Mix sugar and crumbs in 13 x 9 inch glass pyrex dish.
Add margarine.
Microwave just until margarine is melted.
Mix and pat in dish with large spoon.
Mix condensed milk and frozen lemonade concentrate gently with a spoon until thick.
If you want the filling to be a deeper yellow then you may add a drop or two of yellow food coloring.
Pour over the graham cracker crust.
Spread Cool Whip over filling.
Freeze until time to serve.
It will not freeze hard; it will just be really cold.

title: chicken-okra-seafood-gumbo
directions: Peel shrimp uncooked and devein.
Cook chicken with salt and pepper until done.
Remove skin, bone and cube.
Save stock.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, lemon extract and apricot nectar in a large bowl; beat for 3 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayo, eggs and salt and pepper to taste. Carefully fold in broccoli and cheese.
Make topping of crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix butter, sugar, syrup and salt together in microwave.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Pour mixture over popped corn in grocery bag 1/3 full.
Shake to mix.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Shake.
Cook for 30 seconds.
Keep shaking until cooled.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until well blended.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Put a chocolate star on top of each.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Blend the first 8 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Add ingredients in order given.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done.
Cool, peel and dice. Add onions, green peppers, salt and pepper and mix well.
Fry bacon pieces until crisp and drain.
Add 1/2 to salad; mix again. Set rest of bacon aside.

title: sheryl's stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs with a fork until well blended. Stir in Wesson oil, vanilla and lemon rind.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Stamp each cookie with the bottom of a glass dipped first in oil, then in sugar.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in boiling water in saucepan for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine next 7 ingredients in bowl, mixing well. Shape into 8 rolls.
Place on cabbage leaves, rolling to enclose filling.
Place rolls on tomatoes in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked fish
directions: Slice
large onion and lay in greased pan.
Salt and pepper fish
and
lay on top of onion.
Pour tomato sauce and water mixture over fish.
Sprinkle paprika on fish.
Mix bread crumbs, cornbread,
chopped
celery,
onion
and bell pepper. Place dressing around fish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: celery casserole
directions: Parboil celery.
Drain.
Mix celery with next 4 ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fried apples
directions: Core apple and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip in egg; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Fry slowly until brown and tender.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar well.
