Sift in separate bowl the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix in with oil mixture, by hand only.
Batter will be thick.
Add vanilla, apples and walnuts. Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date raisin bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, put in Raisin Bran flakes and pour buttermilk over flakes; let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine rest of ingredients; mix until well blended.
Fill muffin cups quite full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Roll first four ingredients in balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Place chocolate Kiss on after cookies are baked.

title: goody bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and margarine.
Pat into a greased and floured 9x15-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and chocolate chips or nuts. pour this over top of first mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Cut into bars.

title: oriental chicken
directions: In skillet melt butter.
Add chicken and onion.
Brown over medium heat.
Add spices.
Brown 1 minute.
Add water and rice. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: great party cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup nuts . Mix all other ingredients well.
Take a small bowl and line with wax paper.
Pour mixture in bowl.
Cover also with wax paper.
Chill several hours.
Remove onto a serving dish.
Press the reserved walnuts onto ball.
Arrange crackers around outside.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix first 5 items.
Pour in crusts; put in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9-inch cake pans.
Cool; cut layers into and fill with the sour cream, sugar and coconut that has been mixed together.
Reserve 1 cup of the filling and add to the Cool Whip to frost cake.
Then sprinkle coconut on top, if desired.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Set aside.
Mix oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Add to apple mixture.
Soften raisins in a little water; drain.
Add to apple mixture.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: basic fried turtle strips
directions: Mix beaten egg and milk.
Salt and pepper turtle cubes.
Dip into mixture, then roll in flour.
Place in hot oil and cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until it reaches 250° on a candy thermometer or use hard ball method.
While this mixture boils, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add the cream of tartar and beat again.
When the mixture reaches the right temperature, add gradually to the egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Roll out onto wax paper sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Spread on peanut butter. Roll up and let set for 30 minutes before slicing.
Use thread or dental floss to slice.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Could add chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.

title: pretzel oven fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Dip chicken pieces into sour cream which has been combined with lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Roll the chicken pieces in crushed pretzel, coating them completely.
Arrange so not touching in a lightly greased baking dish or pan in a moderate 350° oven until crisp and brown on outside and tender and moist within.

title: tomato juice
directions: Cook tomatoes.
Press through sieve to get the juice.
Boil the tomato juice.
Put into hot jars with 1 teaspoon salt per quart jar.
Seal with hot lids (do not cook).

title: saturday night chicken
directions: Generously sprinkle garlic salt and paprika on both sides of chicken.
Place in one layer in shallow baking dish.
Dilute soup with cream and parsley; pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 1 hour until golden at 350°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Pour into dish.
Refrigerate until it starts to set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Return to refrigerator until firm.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with corn flake crumbs.
Don't get this too hot.
Set aside.
After carrots are cooked, melt 3 tablespoons butter in pan over low heat with 1/3 cup onion, stirring often until onion is softened but not browned.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper and gradually add milk.
Stir until smooth.
Increase heat to medium and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat and add parsley flakes.
Put carrots in a baking dish and pour sauce over top and mix.
Then sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook pudding in milk and let cool.
Soak raisins 5 minutes. Mix all together and pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Beat eggs, butter and 1 1/2 cup of sugar until light. Mix in flour. Mix 2 Tbsp. sugar and cinnamon in a saucer. Shape dough into balls. Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Cut cabbage into small wedges.
Remove bacon from skillet and add cabbage, onion, sugar, water and spices to the bacon drippings.
Cook, covered, over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Add kielbasa that has been cut into bite-size pieces.
Return cover and continue to cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: french toast
directions: In microwave melt butter in bottom of 9 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Layer bread, 2 slices deep on top (the crusts can be cut off).
In separate bowl beat together the eggs and milk.
Pour this over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle maple syrup and broil until brown and bubbly (5 minutes or less).

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets till tender.
Slip skins by putting in cold water. Cut to size desired and put into boiling brine mixture.
Return to boil.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Boil honey, syrup and sugar 1 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir and put out on cookie sheet.

title: margie's chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Roll cubed chicken pieces in seasoned flour.
Brown in margarine.
Add cream of mushroom soup, mixed with water, to chicken and drippings in pan.
Simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown and drain meat, then combine with sauce and spices. Simmer 10 minutes.
Put mixture in buns.
Add cheese on top of mix to melt.

title: beets royale
directions: Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Cook until thickened.
Add vinegar, salt, pineapple and beets.
Heat through until hot.

title: rolled round rump roast
directions: In a roasting pan, pour 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup diluted with water. Put roast in pan, then use the rest of the soup diluted with water over top of roast. Pour package of dry beefy mushroom soup over top of the roast. Let some of the dry soup go into soup in the bottom of roasting pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Boil sliced mushrooms about 3 to 5 minutes in water and about 1 cup lemon juice; drain and cool (this helps to keep them white as will the taste). Break apart cauliflower and broccoli to bite size; mix all ingredients together. Add spices to your taste: celery seed, Mrs. Dash, parsley flakes (dried or fresh), garlic (chopped), oregano, Accent, fresh ground pepper and tarragon leaves. Add 1 to 2 cups of oil, red wine vinegar and 1/2 cup juice from green olives to taste. You can keep this for about a month. Refrigerate; stir often.

title: purple cow
directions: Place cold milk, frozen grape juice concentrate and ice cream in blender.
Cover; blend until smooth and frothy.
Pour into 2 (12-ounce) glasses.
Top with scoops of vanilla ice cream.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 34 to 45 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Dip tortillas in broth and line an 11 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place on top of tortillas in order:
chicken, pepper, onions and mushrooms.
Mix 2 soups together and pour over. Sprinkle with cheese; pour over.
Sprinkle with cheese; pour tomatoes and broth over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mixture will be mealy.
Put crumbs in bottom of a deep 8-inch baked pie shell (save enough crumbs for topping).
Mix pie filling as directed on package and pour over crumbs.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Chill and serve.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Add cheese and soup to hot rice.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Pour boiling water over broccoli in colander and let drain. Add pimento and broccoli to onion and celery.
Add all to rice. Place in buttered casserole and cook in oven at 350° until it bubbles.

title: diabetic banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine shortening, eggs, sweetener and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and stir only until flour is moistened.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Pour into a well-greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain off fat.
Stir in brown sugar and Ragu sauce.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Cook noodles by directions on package.
Spread about 1/2 cup meat sauce in greased 9 x 13-inch deep baking dish.
Layer, starting with noodles, then sauce, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese, ending with Mozzarella cheese, making 2 layers of everything.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach. Mix with all ingredients. Chill. Serve with rye bread or crackers.

title: hearty hodgepodge
directions: In Dutch oven, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Add sliced onion to drippings in pan.
Cook until tender.
Add beef, ham, water and salt.
Cook until tender; remove bone.
Skim fat and return meat to soup.
Add undrained beans, potatoes and garlic.
Simmer for 30 minutes more.
Add thinly sliced Polish sausage and bacon.
Simmer for 15 minutes more.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Serve with buttered toasted French bread.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simply bring milk, water and rice to a boil.
Boil for 40 or 50 minutes (less if recipe is cut in half) or until rice is done and mixture is thick and creamy.
Stir often.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until very frothy.
Add rice mixture slowly to egg mixture and fold.
Chill.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, celery and garlic in oil until vegetables are tender.
Add broth, tomatoes, zucchini, carrot, cabbage, garbanzo beans and rosemary.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes.
Add macaroni; simmer 10 minutes. Garnish each serving with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead dough very well.
Make into biscuits (pinch or roll out).
Place on buttered bread pan.
Also butter the tops of biscuits.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan*.

title: smooth and creamy cheese dip
directions: Place cheese (Velveeta melts the smoothest) in crock-pot and put on low temperature (10 minutes) until softened.
Add salsa and mix well.
Serve warm with dipping fruit and vegetables, tortilla chips or drizzle over toasted tortillas.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with pudding mix.
Stir well and add rest of ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Chill.

title: snow bars
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients cook over low heat in heavy bottom container until smooth, or until dates have dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add 5 or 6 cups of Rice Krispies.
After they are mixed well, spread out in large pan.
Press down; sprinkle with coconut.
While still warm, cut into small squares.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients over low heat.
After mixture is heated through and cheese is melted, add the potatoes. Let set for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered, and then uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Toss the spaghetti with the dressing.
Add all other ingredients, except tomatoes and chill in refrigerator overnight. Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Mix chicken, broccoli and cheese.
Place in casserole dish. Mix cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture. Top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbling.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Best served on top of noodles or macaroni twists.

title: thanksgiving dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dishes sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with gravy and cranberry sauce.
Serves 25.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Put 2 to 3 teaspoonfuls in one cup boiling water.

title: creamy garlic sauce
directions: Place 1/4 cup oil, egg, mustard, salt, lemon juice and garlic in a blender container.
Blend on low and add remaining oil in a steady stream.
Switch to high speed for a few seconds.
Chill. Good served with beef or pork.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients (except peaches) well.
Put into a deep pan.
Pour can of sliced peaches into mixture.
Bake at 350° around 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: quick skillet
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni.
Bring mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to let it simmer.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: microwave wassail
directions: In 3-quart casserole, place all ingredients and microwave on High for 15 to 18 minutes until hot.
Strain and serve.
Makes 8 to 9 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: california mexican dip
directions: Fry chorizo and onion.
Layer in 9 x 15-inch pan in order the first 6 ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Add balance of ingredients in order and serve with corn chips.

title: one layer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in one greased and floured pan at 350° until brown.

title: curried lemon soup
directions: Beat or whisk together water, vinegar, eggs, flour, mustard, salt and pepper in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 6 minutes until smooth and thickened. Stir in margarine and artificial sweetener.
Whisk until smooth. Pour into clean jars.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator up to 3 months.
Makes 3 1/2 cups boiled dressing.
Each serving (2 tablespoons) contains 17 calories.

title: basic roux
directions: Mix flour and oil in heavy pot.
Cook on medium heat slowly, stirring constantly.
The way I make roux takes no less than 30 minutes and up to 45 minutes.
Cook until color of dark chocolate. After you get color desired, add chopped vegetables, ie: onion, celery and bell pepper.
When onions cook clear, add cold water or stock.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In frying pan, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except cheese) and let simmer while preparing crust.
Press dinner roll dough over bottom and up sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon hot meat mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 13 to 18 minutes.

title: spiced chicken
directions: About 1 hour and 15 minutes before serving, peel, seed and dice 6 tomatoes. Cut 3 tomatoes into wedges; set aside.
(This is only if using fresh tomatoes.)
Coat chicken with flour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix gelatin into cottage cheese; fold in Cool Whip until well mixed and then fold in fruit.
Sprinkle top with nuts, cherries or coconut.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of well-greased Bundt pan. Set aside. Combine sugar and cinnamon. Cut biscuits into fourths and shake in bag with sugar and cinnamon. Arrange biscuit pieces in Bundt pan. Combine brown sugar and butter. Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples and pack in jars.
Bring other ingredients to a boil and pour over apples and seal.
Cook for 30 minutes in water bath canner.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop all
ingredients
fine;
mix all together in large pan. Cook 2 hours
on
medium
heat.
Pour
in jars, then put jars in water bath until they are hot enough to seal.

title: cream cheese olive spread
directions: Cream the cream cheese, olives and milk together.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce; mix.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: top-hatter franks
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In hot butter in skillet, saute onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Stir in franks, mustard, soup and milk.
Turn into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Prepare muffin mix as label directs.
Pour over franks mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until corn muffin mix is done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pepper steak(deer meat or beef)
directions: Take the meat.
Put seasoning on it.
Flour it, then brown it in the oil.
When meat is brown, add green bell pepper and onion. Saute them together.
Take beef cube and 2 cups hot water.
Make gravy out of this.
Pour gravy over meat, peppers and onion. Simmer them together for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: missouri cookies(no bake)
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and cocoa in saucepan. Boil and stir mixture for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Then add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Stir very well until mixture thickens. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool. They will then become hard. Store in airtight container to keep longer.

title: simply walnut cookies
directions: Beat butter and 2
tablespoons	sugar
at
medium speed until blended.
Stir in
flour.
Add
walnut
extract and walnuts, stirring well.
Chill
for 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until
done.
Roll
warm cookies in powdered sugar. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: baked oysters
directions: Heat together in a casserole the milk and margarine until margarine melts. Drain the oysters.
Remove casserole from oven and alternate layers of cracker crumbs and oysters to milk. Add more crumbs, if needed, but do not overload.
Keep it slighlty juicy.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cocoa refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add the egg. Sift together flour, salt and cocoa. Add to butter mixture.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in 1 cup chopped nuts. Chill, slice and bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool. Frost with melted sweet chocolate.

title: easy pie
directions: Place fruit in a baking dish.
Mix eggs, butter and sugar.

title: easter salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix jello according to package directions, then stir in pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool until firm.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with the cinnamon and set aside.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Set aside. Combine oil and remaining cup of sugar.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until fluffy and yellow in color.
Add vanilla. Beat well.
Add flour mixture gradually.
Beat until smooth. Spread half of the batter in the bottom of a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Then spread cherry pie filling over batter. Spread the remaining batter over the cherry pie filling layer. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over top. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mary's mother's snowballs
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until smooth.
Add flour, then nuts. Gather dough into disk shape and wrap in plastic.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
Insert 1 kiss into ball of dough 1 inch in diameter.
Make sure kiss is completely covered by dough.
Bake on ungreased sheet about 12 minutes at 350°.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies while still warm.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Blend the Oreo cookies in a blender. Mix the melted butter with the cookies, mixing until moist. Press into 13 x 9 pan. Freeze for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: In a large bowl, lightly beat the eggs. Stir together the sugar, salt and flour and very gradually beat into the eggs. Add the melted butter, vanilla and milk and mix until smooth. Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until custard tests done. Let cool before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix corn, pimento, bell pepper, onion and celery together in salad bowl.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over corn mixture.
Stir well and refrigerate.
This is better if allowed to marinate a day or two.

title: raspberry poke cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom of pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, with shortening. Make cake mix. Pour in pan. Bake 28 to 33 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool completely, about 1 hour. Pierce cake every 1/2-inch with fork. Stir gelatin and boiling water in small bowl until smooth; stir in cold water. Pour over cake. Run knife around side of pan to loosen it. Refrigerate 2 hours. Spread whipped topping over top of cake; garnish with raspberries. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: pizza hot dogs
directions: Split hot dog buns and hot dogs lengthwise.
Place layer of cheese on buns.
Add hot dog slices to each bun.
Top with pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place on broiler pan. Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: this bait will catch your fish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough cold water to form a stiff ball.
Knead until well mixed.
Pinch off pieces the size of grapes.
Roll into balls.
Boil water with 1/4 onion in saucepan. Remove onion pieces and discard when the water boils.
Pour dough balls into boiling water and cook until they rise to the surface. Takes only 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove the balls and lay them out to cool and harden.
They will keep for days and can be placed in dampened cloth before using to soften them up.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder, and salt together. Melt butter in baking dish and pour in batter.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Cut zucchini in half, remove center.
Blanch or cook in boiling salted water until almost done.
In skillet, put oil, chopped garlic, chopped pepper, chopped onion and burger; brown slightly. Add bread crumbs and may add some of zucchini centers, not the seeds.
May need to add a little milk or water if too dry and saute another 5 minutes.
Stuff the zucchini boats.
Put in pan and add cheese on top.
Bake until brown and cheese melted.
May be made into patties and served with tomato sauce.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put in deep vessel and cook until mixture threads (sugar, water and syrup).
Add peanuts; cook until they pop.
Remove from heat; add soda and wax.
Stir well.
Pour in pans thinly.
Break into pieces when cool.
Be sure to butter pans before pouring in mixture.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake about 20 minutes at 300°. Cut while hot.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Sift soda, nutmeg and flour together.
Beat eggs; add sugar, cream, butter and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon unto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: pumpkin-pecan loaf
directions: Combine margarine and white and brown sugars.
Add eggs and blend.
Add pumpkin and blend.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in nuts if desired.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water over medium heat (using heavy saucepan) to hard-ball stage.
In the meantime, beat egg whites and salt until stiff but still glossy.
Pour syrup into egg white mixture in thin stream while beating until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix cake mix and lemon filling together with wooden spoon.
Put in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown and springs back when tapped with finger.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: savory dried beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, then let stand in cooking water for a few minutes to swell.
Drain and rinse.
Frizzle shredded dried beef in butter.
Add noodles to dried beef, then heat soup and milk together.
Pour over other ingredients and pour mixture into a casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Add just enough milk to make a good dip consistency.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 3 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: alice chicken
directions: To Marinate:

Place chicken in a nonporous glass dish or bowl. Poke with a fork several times, then pour Worcestershire sauce over chicken. Turn pieces to coat on both sides. Cover dish and refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Blend the cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it is thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and eggs.
Spoon chicken mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll out pastry on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut pastry into 3/4-inch wide strips using a fluted pastry wheel.
Arrange strips, lattice fashion, across top.
Combine raw egg and water. Lightly brush pastry with egg mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together. Sift flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture and beat well. Fold in zucchini and nuts. Pour batter into two greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy angel cake
directions: Sift together the flour packet and the spices.
Prepare and bake according to package directions.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix together sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed, paprika, garlic and pepper. Stir chicken breast into bowl of marinade; coat well. Marinate overnight.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla and flour. Roll out on a floured board.
Cut into size desired.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cook as described on box, except instead of water add the mandarin orange juice.
Put into 3 layers and cook 30 minutes. Cool.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and other ingredients. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until done.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix package of Jell-O with 1 cup hot water. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into strips.	Brown in skillet.
Mix cream of mushroom
soup,
water
and
onion	soup
together; stir until smooth.
Add it into pot of steak.	Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Add sour cream just before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add onions.
Cook until transparent. After draining off grease from meat, mix well with soups.
Add cooked noodles.
Place
mixture
in large casserole dish.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, then cauliflower.
Drain frozen peas until thawed and dry, then mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Pour this on top, then sprinkle with sugar, bacon bits and cheese.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Blend shortening with hot water and sugar.
Add oleo, eggs (one at a time), flour and milk.
Beat all together for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Use well-floured, greased angel food pan.

title: meat noodle casserole
directions: Cook, drain and rinse egg noodles. Brown ground beef in small amount of oil; add onions, celery, green pepper and salt and pepper to meat and cook until tender (add a little water to prevent sticking). Combine beef mixture and noodles and pour into casserole dish. Pour tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce and cheese on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry
ingredients,
then add wet ingredients and mix well.
Bake in well gread muffin pans at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Unused
batter may be stored in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Put initial starter
in
fridge
for
3 to 5 days, then take out and
feed
with potatoes, sugar and water.
Let stand out of fridge all day, 8 to 10 hours.

title: hamburger cassoulet
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, pepper and egg. Shape into 32 tiny balls.
Dredge with flour.
Bring bouillon, water, tomatoes, 1 teaspoon of salt and bay leaf to boil in pot. Add meat balls and barley.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add rice during last 15 minutes.

title: chocolate covered marshmallows
directions: Melt and mix Eagle Brand milk, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme over low heat.
Stir until completely blended.
Use ice tongs to dip marshmallows.
Completely coat and set on waxed paper to cool.
They may be frozen for later use.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Add soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup grated cheese, celery and onion; mix.
Sprinkle top with Ritz crackers and grated cheese.
Pour one stick of melted margarine on top. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook meal, salt, sugar and milk over medium heat until thickened.
Beat eggs and baking powder together with corn meal mixture.
Add butter, melted in a deep baking dish.
Pour mixture into buttered dish and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cool and simple citrus pie
directions: Place lemonade in large mixing bowl and beat about 30 seconds. Gradually spoon in ice cream and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip and add food coloring, whipping until smooth.
Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening, eggs and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes.
Add cocoa and nuts; beat 1 minute longer until smooth.
Spread in greased and floured pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and cocoa to a boil, stirring every few minutes.
Turn off heat; add peanut butter.
Stir until melted. Add vanilla, salt and stir.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Stir until well blended.
Mixture will look sticky in appearance.
Spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool for one half hour to one hour.
Cookies will set up as they cool.

title: drop donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop batter in hot vegetable oil by spoonful.
When brown, put on plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Butter potatoes while hot and add the onions that have been sauteed in oleo. Add mayonnaise, bacon, cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper, garlic salt and garlic powder. Mix all ingredients together and put back into potato skins. Put in 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour into churn.
Finish filling with homogenized milk.

title: poor man's dinner
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Season with pepper and garlic powder.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, thinly layer the beef, potatoes and onion slices.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Mix the eggs and the sugar together.
Add the fruit mixture. Add enough water (cold) to make a gallon.
Freeze as you would for homemade ice cream.

title: chili that tommy will eat
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Add onion and cook until tender; drain.
Add 1/2 cup water to chili mix and stir.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on high for 2 hours or cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: leroy's super potato soup
directions: For less ruffles, use 1 cup flour and 1 egg.

title: krispy kandy
directions: Melt white chocolate like package says.
Mix in Rice Krispies, pretzels and pecans.
Spread out flat on wax paper; let harden, about 30 minutes.

title: enchilada pie casserole
directions: Brown
ground
beef
with
diced onions and seasonings, then drain.
Heat
enchilada
sauce in pan.
Heat tortillas in oil and drain.
Dip
in sauce.
Layer tortillas, ground beef, corn and sour
cream
in
a 13 x 9-inch glass casserole dish. Pour enchilada sauce over layer and spread out.	Add a mixture of cheese.
Repeat
once
more.
Bake	casserole in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in pecans.
Will make 2 good size balls.

title: poulet cordon bleu
directions: Cut chicken breasts into halves.
Place chicken between 2 pieces plastic wrap.
Pound with mallet until 1/4 inch thick. Place 1 slice ham and cheese on each piece of chicken.
Roll up carefully, beginning at narrow end.
Secure with wooden picks. Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat rolls with flour mixture, dip them into egg, roll in bread crumbs.
In a 10 inch skillet heat oil over medium heat until hot.
Cook rolls in oil until light brown, turning occasionally about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add water, cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 10 minutes.
When serving, remove picks.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple; let set overnight. Mix sugar and flour together. Stir in egg. In a saucepan, bring pineapple juice to a boil over medium heat. Slowly now, add egg, sugar and flour. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in pineapple, then stir in cheese.

title: ridiculously simple banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a loft pan and bake at 3350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook together for 15 minutes.
Add cream and cook until potatoes are tender.
Serve hot. Garnish with parsley (optional).
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel potatoes.
Bake for 1 hour, or until tender.
Mash potatoes.
Add 1/4 cup orange juice, margarine, salt, pepper and ginger.
Stir orange juice into the potato mixture.
Put into greased casserole dish; bake for 15 minutes, or until heated.
Serves 8.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown sausage or ground chuck and onions.
Drain off grease. Spray casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray or grease dish. Layer sauce, meats, noodles, onions and cheeses.
Finish off with sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soft taco
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and add taco seasoning.
Fix appropriate number of servings of rice.
Cut lettuce and tomato into small pieces.
Cut cheese into cubes and place in microwavable bowl.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes to cheese and melt in microwave.
Then layer ingredients (rice, meat, Fritos, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese mixture, sour cream and any other toppings you prefer) on plate and serve.

title: tuna - cheese salad
directions: Prepare macaroni cheese dinner by package directions. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: eagle brand pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extract. Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Add Eagle brand milk and combine with batter.
Bake at 300° approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: odd candy
directions: Melt chocolate.
Stir in noodles, peanuts and chips.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: crab delish
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, green onions and milk.
Add crabmeat.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° until bubbly. Can be spread on thin rounds of French bread.
Serve hot.

title: clam dip appetizer
directions: Melt butter, then add next 7 ingredients until onion and garlic are soft.
Add minced clams with juice, bread crumbs and cheese. Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: In mixing bowl, beat butter or margarine, peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar with electric mixer until combined. Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Add to mixing bowl. Beat at low speed until just combined. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in greased 1 3/4-inch muffin pan. Bake in 350° oven for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Catalina dressing overnight.
Place chicken breasts in greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Serve with extra warm Catalina dressing.
Chicken may be cooked on a grill instead of in an oven.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Melt oleo.
Add sour cream.
Add Cheddar cheese (grated) and cream of mushroom soup.
Place in casserole and crumble cornflakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low cholesterol pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center of filling comes out clear.
Cool.
(If using frozen pie shells, this recipe fills 2 shells.)

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli in bite
size pieces.
Add in onions and pimento.
Mix together
remaining
ingredients. Add peas and mix.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs, syrup, Pet cream and vanilla. Add broken pecans and mix.
Pour into a pie crust and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients lightly, do not pack.
Place on rack in baking pan.
Spread top with ketchup.
Bake in 350° oven for about one hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix broken pretzels with melted margarine and 1/3 cup sugar. Put into bottom of 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: granny's lye soap
directions: Melt grease and let cool.
Pour water on lye and let get cool, stirring until dissolved.
Add Borax to the lye.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the lye to the grease and stir 7 minutes.
Then add ammonia and stir 3 minutes longer.
(The more you stir the whiter the soap will be.)
Let set until hard.
Takes about 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Press out rolls on round pizza pan.
Spread sausage, sprinkle cheese, then pour beaten eggs and milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: one dish chicken and rice bake
directions: Mix soup, water, rice and spices in 2 qt. shallow baking dish.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika and pepper.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 45-60 minutes.
Stir lightly before serving.
Yield 4 servings.
A warm and hearty dish for cool nights.

title: herbed oven potatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl. Combine the first six ingredients. Add potatoes, a few at a time; toss to coat. Place in a single layer in a greased 15x10 inch baking pan. Drizzle with remaining oil mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 450 degrees for 50-55 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with parsley. Yield: 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 8.

title: sugarplum pudding
directions: Mix oil and milk together, set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients together, add eggs (beaten).
Add salad oil, milk prunes and chopped nuts. Bake in 325 degree oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken recipe
directions: To a casserole which has onion flakes on bottom, add chicken. In a large bowl, beat soup with soy sauce and 7-Up or Sprite. Beat with eggbeater and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then turn oven to 250° for one hour.
Try it, you'll like it.

title: braised pot roast
directions: Season the meat with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place on a shallow baking pan. Strew the onions around the meat and brown in a 425° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with flour and return to the oven for 10 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: In a clean flowerpot, alternate layers of Oreo crumbs and filling mixture, beginning and ending with crumbs.

title: caramel apples
directions: Mix honey and evaporated milk together.
Cook, stirring constantly, to firm-ball stage or to 255° on a candy thermometer. Stir in vanilla, butter and salt.
Dip apples into caramel.
Spoon excess from bottom.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Chill until caramel is firm.

title: brown rice and sausage
directions: Slice sausage into rounds. Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry out slices of salt pork in a 2-quart saucepan, then add to this the water, onion and potatoes.
Cook until tender. Pour
in the
can
of clams, juice and milk.
Season to taste with
salt and pepper and add the butter.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil. Serves 2.

title: roast pork flamande
directions: Toast caraway seed in dry small skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Rub pork with coarse salt, thyme, paprika, marjoram and pepper.
Make slits, about 3/4-inch deep and 2 inches apart, in surface of pork with a small sharp knife. Insert bits of minced garlic and the caraway seed into slits.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in sour milk or buttermilk and bananas.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add nutmeats.
Put in loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix
flour,
margarine,
milk
and brown sugar together. Bake in
small
pan
for
20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Crumble up and press in 8 x 10-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and Cool
Whip together.
Put
over
crust and top with cherry pie filling.

title: chocolate cream fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and chocolate syrup.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Serve with fruit.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, cut into quarters.
Add mayonnaise, cheese and mix.
Place in casserole dish; refrigerate until ready to bake.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let scalded milk cool.
Add remaining ingredients and 5 cups of flour.
Add flour as needed. Let rise in warm area for 30 minutes.
Roll out dough.
Cut into doughnuts.
Fry.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup until sugar has dissolved.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate morsels and butterscotch morsels.
Pour over mixture.
Cool and slice.

title: parmesan-crusted swiss steak
directions: Score steak, making diagonal cuts about 1/2-inch in diameter. Mix flour, seasoned salt, paprika, coffee and garlic powder. Rub well into both sides of meat.
In pan, heat shortening; brown meat.
Add onion, bouillon and wine.
Cover and simmer meat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat and thicken gravy with 1 teaspoon of cornstarch.
Combine cheese and mayonnaise.
Place over meat.
Slip under broiler until glazed and brown.
Serve steak with gravy.

title: crepes
directions: Put the flour and salt in a bowl; stir in the milk, drop in the eggs and beat the mixture with an eggbeater or a whisk until it's smooth.
It should be the consistency of a runny milkshake.
Put the batter in a pitcher so you can pour it into the pan.
You cook the crepes one at a time in a small frying pan.
Grease the pan with a tiny dab of butter or margarine.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in well-greased, large Bundt pan at 350°.
To make a drizzle to pour over cake after baking, mix a generous 1/2 cup sifted confectioners sugar with enough lemon juice to make it flow.

title: coconut peanut butter bars
directions: Grease 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix oleo, peanut butter and sugar until blended.
Stir in eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in flour mixture, then coconut.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 3/4-inch bars.
If desired, roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Makes 32.

title: doris' crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot overnight on low. Remove and debone; set aside. Mix together crumbled corn bread, toasted white bread, sage, pepper, salt, onion, celery seed and chopped celery. To this mixture, add cream of chicken soup, chicken broth and beaten eggs; add to broth in crock-pot and stir to blend (may be thin, but not to worry). Place chicken on top of dressing in crock-pot; cook on high temperature for 3 1/2 hours.

title: nutty cheese cookies(sugarless recipe)
directions: Fill locking plastic bag with ketchup or mustard.
Add tape to close bag.
Flatten.
Your child can "paint" on surface of bag "erase" by smoothing.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Let set 1 hour.
Crush the Oreo cookies.

title: hamburger chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onions.
Add remaining ingredients, but only 1/2 noodles.
Place rest on top in oven or when ready to serve.
Bake in a greased 2-quart casserole dish, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry sweetheart salad
directions: Drain pineapple (juice can be used in place of some of the water).
Bring 2 cups of water or combination of juice and water to a boil.
Dissolve gelatin in liquid.
Stir in pineapple, bananas, pecans and strawberries.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish or large heart mold.
When chilled, spread sour cream over salad and top with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until set.
Garnish with more sour cream, if desired.

title: cream cheese finger cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and cream cheese.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine the flour, sugar and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans (dough will be crumbly).
Shape tablespoons full into 2 in. logs.
Place 2 in. apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 minutes until lightly browned.
Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar; cool on wire racks.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: monica's cinnamon pickles
directions: Mix 8 1/2 quarts of water and 2 cups white powdered lime.
Stir occasionally.
Wash, peel and cut into strips large ripe cucumbers that have the seeds removed, about 4-5 quarts prepared cucumber strips.

title: metropolitan cheap sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add sugar gradually, continue beating.
Add water and dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites and vinegar into batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water well.
Add Crisco, sugar and 1/2 of flour. Add beaten egg and salt.
Add remaining flour and let rise 2 hours.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter; place on baking sheet.
Let rise 2 more hours and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
They can be cooked about 5 minutes, frozen, then finish baking when needed.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Add sugar to beaten egg until sugar is dissolved.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts, apples and almond extract.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fresh vegetable supreme
directions: In large skillet or saucepan, put all vegetables.
In small bowl, mix water, Sip'r Seez'n and oil.
Pour over vegetables. Cover; steam 5 minutes.
Add chicken style chunks; steam 5 minutes.
Serve over brown rice with soy sauce.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and drain very well.
Combine the spinach, sour cream and onion soup in buttered casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs, butter and cheese.
Put cracker mixture over top of spinach.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In heavy pot, place first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil, lower heat to slow boil.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring constantly.
Last 5 minutes, add from blender last 3 ingredients (sugar, vanilla, eggs).
Slowly stir in blended eggs.
Take off heat.
Let stand to cool.
Place in dessert dishes.
Add cinnamon.

title: homemade seasoned rice mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Store in an airtight container for up to 6 months. Stir well before each use.
Makes 3 cups.

title: breakfast in a muffin pan
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12 muffin cups.
Press about 2 tablespoons hash in each of 6 muffin cups, making deep indentation in center of hash.
Break an egg into each hash cup; season with salt and pepper.
Prepare half package of muffin mix as directed; fill remaining muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until muffins are golden brown and eggs are desired doneness.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: elk or venison loin roast
directions: Split the loin lengthwise but not clear through.
Into the split shake some salt and pepper and garlic powder.
Your taste preference will determine how much.
Add the onions and mushrooms to the split, pushing them into the cavity as far as possible. Wrap bacon, spiral-fashion, around the roast, securing with toothpicks, to hold roast tightly together.
Wrap in heavy weight aluminum foil.
Bake in a moderate-slow oven (325°) for about 20 to 30 minutes per pound.
When done, open foil and place under the broiler for a few minutes to brown, if desired.
Slice meat into 1/4 to 1/3-inch slices.
Serve with au jus, if you like, or if you think it is too dry.
You'll find this combination delicious.

title: butterscotch apple crumb pie
directions: Make a 1 crust pie shell.
Fill with apples sliced very thin and piled high as they tend to shrink.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix in a separate bowl the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt. Blend and sprinkle over layers of apples.
Cover edge of pie crust with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Put sugar on stove in
enough water to dissolve and let come to a boil.	Drop in figs
and
boil
until tender or so a straw sticks through them
easily.
Take	figs
out
and leave syrup to cook on longer.
Drop
in
a
few
slices of lemon to boil in syrup.
Boil syrup until it spins a thread.
Drop figs back in and cook a few	minutes
longer.
Take	up and seal in jars.

title: cream spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl combine sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning. Stir in onion, spinach, water chestnuts and red pepper.
Cover. Refrigerate to blend flavor.
Serve with crisp vegetable dippers, assorted crackers or bread.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: gene's cheese wafers
directions: Grate cheese and cream with oleo.
Add the dry ingredients. Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.
Press flat with the back of a fork.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch beans
directions: Drain ground beef and combine with all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lucy's pudding cake
directions: Mix.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix ingredients, adding apples and nuts.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: curry beef stew
directions: Slice onions thin or chop.
Brown in Crisco; add meat and cook until done, but not browned.
Add chopped green onions, all spices and then tomatoes.
Cook over slow fire for 1/2 hour.
Five minutes before serving, add vinegar and sugar.
Let cook 5 minutes.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Pound chicken into thin cutlets.
Slightly beat egg with water.
Mix Herb Blend with bread crumbs or use Brownberry Herb stuffing mix.
Dip cutlets in egg mixture, then in seasoned bread crumbs.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
In nonstick baking dish, arrange chicken cutlets and drizzle each with melted margarine and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dutch salad dressing
directions: Fry bacon over low heat until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Mix egg, water, vinegar and onion. Add to sugar mixture and add all to bacon drippings.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add crumbled bacon.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut beef into strips (2 x 1 x 1/4-inch). Heat oil in large skillet.
Add beef; cook, turning frequently, until brown, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, onion, garlic salt and ginger.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Add green peppers during last 5 minutes of simmering.
While beef is simmering, cook rice.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce; stir into beef mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Cut each tomato into eighths; place on beef mixture. Cover; cook over low heat just until tomatoes are heated through. Serve with rice.

title: albondiga soup
directions: Dice potatoes.

Mix hamburger and rice together. Make into 12-14 balls then fry lightly in frying pan. Transfer into a large sauce pan and add 2 c. water and taco mix. Simmer for 45 min. Then add potatoes and simmer for 20 more min.
Add beans stewed tomatoes (juice too), simmering for about another 30-35 min. or until potatoes are cooked. Serve alone or with cooked rice.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll each biscuit into 3-inch circle; cut in half.
Wrap apple quarter in each half biscuit.
Place in baking dish.
Bring sugar, water and margarine to a boil.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Cool about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix together.
Dip smelt or other fish in batter and fry in hot grease.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown the beef in a skillet; drain off all grease.
Combine salt, pepper and chili powder in a small container.
Mix well. Mix together chili sauce and ketchup in a large container.
Stir well.
Mix in salt, pepper, chili powder and onions.
Mix well. Now add the ground beef.
Slowly bring the ingredients to a boil. Lower heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let cool. Store in plastic containers and freeze.
Makes 50 servings.

title: grilled ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Warm slice of ham in frying pan.
Take out and put on slice of bread.
Top with slice of cheese and other slice of bread.
Using butter, fry one side until brown.
Turn over and do other side. Cut in half and serve.

title: quick pie crust
directions: Mix well with a fork.
Form into a ball.
Roll out between 2 layers of wax paper and put in a pie plate.

title: strawberry graham dessert
directions: In small bowl, combine cracker crumbs and butter; set aside 1 Tbsp. for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture into 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 14 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool.

title: cranberry glazed chicken
directions: Combine 1/2 cup flour and salt. Dredge chicken in flour. Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and cook 30 minutes until golden brown. Remove, drain on paper towels. Add cranberries, brown sugar and water to pan drippings. Cook for 5 minutes. Blend cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour together; add vinegar. Combine vinegar mixture with cranberry mixture; cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Return chicken to mixture in skillet. Baste with cranberry mixture. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, turning chicken occasionally. Serve with rice.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain thawed berries.
To juice, add lemon juice and enough water to make 1 cup of liquid. Add to gelatin with salt and chill until mixture thickens slightly. Fold in whipped cream, cake cubes and berries.
Chill until firm. Serves 10.

title: crock-pot roast beef dinner
directions: Put potatoes
and
carrots
in bottom of 5 quart crock-pot. Add water.
Salt
and
pepper
roast and place on top of potatoes. Lay
onion
and
garlic slices on roast.
Cover and cook on high for 6 hours.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover the chicken with water in a large pan.
Leave the skin on and boil until
the chicken is tender.
Remove the chicken from the pan.
Remove the skin and bones.
Cut the chicken into chunks; put it back into broth and bring to a boil.
Cut the tortillas into strips.
Drop the strips into the boiling broth a few at a time until all have been added.
Stir gently as you drop the strips in.
When all have been added, cover the pan and turn off the heat.
If juice is too thick, add a little milk.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Combine biscuit mix and water; mix until soft dough forms.
Knead on floured board until it can be handled.
Press into pan.
Spread ham, green chilies and olives over crust.
Mix eggs, sour cream, cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour over ham.
Bake for 25 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Salt and pepper steak and roll in flour. Lightly brown steak in hot oil. Drain off remaining oil and saute onions in skillet. Then add Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes over meat and onions. Cover with a lid and cook on low heat for 1 hour. Serve over rice. Will serve 4 to 6 people.

title: hummus
directions: Blend all ingredients together (except the olive oil) in food processor until smooth.
Add oil and mix well.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Serve with crackers or cut pieces of pita bread.

title: homemade pasta
directions: In large bowl combine 1 cup flour, 1/3 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Use mixer on low speed.
Beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
With wooden spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and not sticky, approximately 20 times.
Roll and cut.
Makes enough dough for 1 pound pasta.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saut onion in butter.
Add flour; mix well.
Boil milk and chicken broth.
Add top ingredients into milk, then add Cheddar cheese, salt, pepper and mustard.
Return to boiling stage.

title: sprouted lentil casserole
directions: *To sprout lentils:
Soak overnight in a jar.
In the morning, rinse lentils and invert jar.
(Use nylon stocking or screen to fit top of a wide mouth jar.)
Keep sprouts in a dark, cool place and rinse 2 times a day.
Sprouts are ready to use when they are 1/2 to 1 inch long (2 to 3 days).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken; let cool and dice.
Put in bottom of greased dish.
Mix together the chicken broth and soup; add to chicken. Drain Veg-All; add to chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients; spread across dish.
Bake at 400° for an hour.
(Will not be really brown when brought out of the oven.)

title: fried okra
directions: Combine okra, milk, and seasonings in a shallow dish; let stand 1 hour or until most of milk is absorbed.
Dredge in cornmeal.
Fry okra in deep hot oil (375 degrees) until golden brown.
Drain.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: dad's famous saturday morning waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil.
Then mix all ingredients together.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a casserole dish (spray with Pam), cook hamburger (brown) and place in casserole dish 1st.
Add the corn 2nd, then 1/2 of soup and milk mixture, then Tater Tots, then cheese, then rest of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes and serve.

title: goblin's delight cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Fill paper muffin cups 2/3 full with batter.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon filling into each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the three ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet and press with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix sugars, eggs, salt and margarine in double boiler and heat just until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well and put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° until light crust forms on top.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top. Let cool and cut in squares.

title: tiropites(cheese triangles)
directions: Beat cheeses until creamy (use mixer).
Add eggs one at a time. Cut dough into 4 parts.
Put sheets all together (filo dough comes in sheets) to keep from drying out.
Put a teaspoon of filling in corner of buttered piece of filo dough.
Roll into a triangle, sealing with melted butter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven or freeze between double sheets of wax paper.
Bake frozen for 1/2 hour.
Makes 80 small.

title: fox head pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Cover with whipped cream to serve.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix ingredients and add 1 cup of the saved juice (if necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup). Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden at the edges.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350° (convection oven: 325°).
Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour (do not use self-rising flour in this recipe).
Make into a ball and roll between two pieces of waxed paper, 1/2 to 1/3-inch thick.
Cut into small shapes (leaves, ovals, squares, rounds, triangles, etc.) with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1/2-inch apart.
Bake approximately 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately and place on wire racks to cool.
Makes about 2 dozen 1 1/2 x 1-inch cookies.

title: moose goop
directions: Set oven to 300°.
In a large ovenproof container, mix meat, soup, wine and soup mix.
Cover and place in oven for as long as you wish (no less than 2 hours and no more than 4 hours).
Remove from oven; stir in mushrooms and sour cream.
If mixture is too thin, stir in 2 tablespoons cornstarch, dissolved in a little water, and simmer slightly.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine milk and juice.
Add nuts, coconut and drained pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into two graham cracker crusts pie shells (already prepared).
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to directions.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Mix well until mixture thickens.
Using a 9 x 9-inch pan, layer whole graham crackers on bottom of pan.
Pour mixture on top.
Add another layer of crackers and pour rest of mixture.
Top with blueberry filling.
Chill before serving.

title: cooked rice pudding
directions: Boil milk, rice and sugar for 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Beat egg and add heavy cream.
Beat a little longer.
Add this to rice mixture and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Blend and chill.

title: grape salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, miracle whip, sour cream, and vanilla, with a mixer, until creamy and smooth.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Chill, serve.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine oats, sugar, salt, softened butter and well beaten eggs.
Mix well together.
Pour into unbaked pastry pie shell. Bake in 350° oven until center of pie doesn't shake, approximately 40 minutes.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Combine beef and onions in skillet; cook until lightly brown. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili salsa and taco sauce mix. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Grease casserole and cover bottom of baking dish with torn pieces of tortillas.
Place layer of shredded cheese and meat sauce; repeat ending with meat sauce on top.
Cover with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Roll into balls the size of walnut. Place balls about 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork dipped in flour, making a crisscrossed pattern. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a jar and shake.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in large saucepan according to package directions; drain.
Add soup, milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: tropical salad bar
directions: In small saucepan, bring vinegar and lime juice to a boil. Add sugar, salt, mustard, celery seed and paprika.
Whisk in oil and onion.
Chill.
Put greens in bowl.
Mix fruit and place on greens.
Drizzle on dressing.
Top with chilled dressing.

title: spinach vegetable dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package. Drain spinach well and squeeze out excess water.
Mix with sour cream and soup mix by hand. Add the scallions, cut small.
Mix.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve as a dip for raw vegetables (cucumbers, celery, carrots, broccoli).

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Put in an airtight container and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Shape into two rolls and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Melt butter in large casserole.
Grate potatoes and cheese. Mix together with butter, sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough in microwave for 2 minutes on medium power. Roll out to a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Do not flour surface. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Place half the pepperoni in rows on each rectangle.
Sprinkle cheese over dough.
Roll up like a nut roll, tuck ends under and place seam side down on greased cookie sheet and let rise a little more.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: gourmet delight
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Pour over dressing.
Chill.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Yields 18 to 20 servings.

title: lacy crab puffs
directions: Heat the oil to 375 degrees.
Drain the crabmeat and reserve 1/4 cup of the liquid.
Combine the reserved liquid with the baking powder.
This will foam so be sure your container is large enough to handle it.
Set aside. Combine the crabmeat, onion, Old Bay seasoning and egg.
Mix well. Add the flour and mix. Stir in the baking powder mixture.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil
Cook until puffs are browned on both sides.
Drain well on absorbent paper.
The puffs will look lacy due to the baking powder.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Put meat back in frying pan and add seasoning mix.
Prepare per directions on package.
After completion of cooking time, place hamburger meat in casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on top of meat.
Add shredded lettuce, tomato or other veggies, if desired.
Pour 1/2 of taco sauce over all.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over mixture.
Top with sour cream, black olives and rest of taco sauce.
Use chips to dip salad.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake
cake
as	directed
on
package in a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Let cool.
Prepare pudding as directed using 1
cup milk.
Add cream cheese; mix well.	Fold in Cool Whip. Spread
on cake
and sprinkle pineapple, nuts and cherries on top.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Fry thick pork chops until brown.
Add sliced potatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with water and boil until water cooks down to gravy.
Add more water while cooking if needed.

title: popcorn crunch
directions: Melt butter and add Karo and sugar.
Blend well.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Boil for 15 minutes, adding pecans and peanuts the last 10 minutes.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread on foil to cool. Once cooled, break apart and store in an airtight container.

title: kanuck's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; change water.
Add soda and salt pork. Parboil until skins break.
Put beans in bean pot; add the salt pork and onion.
Add mustard, sugar and molasses.
Cover with bean water.
Bake all day or overnight
in 250° oven which was preheated.
Add water after about 6 hours if needed.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Bring chicken parts to a boil in a large pot with tight fitting cover with enough water to cover (at least 6 cups). About 20 minutes after chicken starts to boil, toss in potatoes and carrots, then about 5 to 10 minutes, toss in peas and chicken bouillon.

title: potato snowballs
directions: Grate about 6 potatoes on the fine side of your potato grater. Strain the grated potatoes through cheesecloth, squeezing fairly dry.
Save the liquid and allow it to settle.
Pour off the water and save the starch that settles in the bottom of the container. Add this starch to the grated potatoes and add one egg.
Season with salt and pepper and add flour as needed, mixing well.
Shape into balls and drop into boiling, salted water.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Pour milk and butter or fried bacon over snowballs and serve warm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter; add water and chicken seasoning. Bring to a boil, stirring until dissolved.
Add noodles.
Cook a few minutes (covered).
Add broccoli.
Cook 15 minutes.
Now add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken (broken or strips) and broccoli.
Mix soup and all other ingredients together. Layer broken Ritz crackers, grated cheese, Ritz crackers on top and 1 stick melted butter.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: citrus salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350°.
If you bake in a coffee can, bake 1 hour; if you bake in small loaf pan, bake 40 minutes.

title: zesty chicken bake
directions: Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan. Saute onion.
Add seasoning and mushroom liquid.
Blend in chicken soup and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
In large bowl, mix rice, mushrooms, pimiento and cubed chicken.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with Cheddar and Parmesan cheese.
Garnish with whole mushrooms and pimiento strips.
Bake in a moderate (350°) oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly brown on top.

title: cherry deluxe rolls
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Add flavorings and mix.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Add salmon (drained and broken in large pieces). Add all other ingredients; toss gently.

title: papaya pineapple juice
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high until smooth.
Makes 2 (12 ounce) servings.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients except eggs for 2 or 3 minutes or until mixture coats back of spoon.
Then add eggs.
Cook for 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Do not boil.

title: my irish mother's chicken soup
directions: Rinse chicken parts thoroughly in cold running water. Place in large soup pot and add cold water to cover chicken. Add vegetables and spices. Bring to a boil and simmer for 3 hours. Remove foam from top while cooking. After cooking, strain soup and discard all chicken parts. Cool overnight in refrigerator. Remove and discard fat. Soup can now be reheated and served or frozen in ice cube trays to add to gravy or other recipes, or freeze in portions for instant chicken soup. Add cooked noodles, if desired.

title: tako poki
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix with hands. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Serves 4.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, nuts, sugar, butter and salt.
Blend together and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on top of first layer.
Mix pudding and milk as directed and spread on top of second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti casserole(spaghetti for a crowd!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (170°C).
Butter a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Cook spaghetti in lightly salted water according to package directions.
Put half of cooked spaghetti in bottom of prepared casserole.
Sprinkle with half the sugar.
Sprinkle half the grated cheese on top, then half the Ready Hamburger Mix, then half the mushrooms.
Repeat layers.
In a small bowl, combine tomato soup, milk and spaghetti sauce.
Pour over entire casserole.
If necessary, add more milk during baking to keep casserole moist.
Bake 1 hour, until bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender or food processor.
Top with cover and process 30 seconds.
To store refrigerate mixture in a covered container up to 1 week or freeze in an airtight container up to 1 month.
Makes 1 cup (88 calories per 1/4 cup serving).

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in a baking dish.
Top with white cake mix, dot with butter over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Nuts may be added.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Remove meat from chickens, then add soup, vegetables, salt and enough evaporated milk to get desired thickness.
Heat through and serve over rice, noodles, biscuits, mashed potatoes or pastry shell.
Freezes well, too.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake in two layers.
Cut into 4 layers.
Place cut side up and frost with the following.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut up dried beef.
Mix cream cheese, green onion tops, Accent, Worcestershire sauce and 1 package of beef.
Roll into ball.
Take other package of cut up dried beef and put on wax paper.
Take cheese ball and roll in dried beef.

title: chicken, broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Place cubed chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook frozen vegetables, drain, then put on top of chicken.
Sprinkle onion on top of vegetables.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add strawberries and pineapple with juice. Pour half of mixture in 9 x 13 pan and chill until set. Spoon sour cream over it and put remaining jello mixture on top. Chill. Serves about 15.

title: hot pan salad
directions: Layer in the following order:

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream
the
sugar
and	oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add wafers and milk alternately.
Add coconut
and
pecans.
Pour
into
greased	tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Fry in oil.
Pour off all grease. Put soup plus 1 can water to cover meat balls.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.	Let set in refrigerator 6 hours.
Serve.

title: chinese new york rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until tender and lightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until heated through.

title: glass cake
directions: Dissolve each Jello in 1-1/4 cups of boiling water, place in small cubed ice trays* and put in refrigerator. In a large bowl, dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup of cold water. Heat pineapple juice to hot but not boiling, pour into unflavored gelatin and stir well, set aside to cool. Crush vanilla wafers, combine with sugar and melted butter, press one half of mixture onto bottom of pan. Fold Cool Whip into gelatin mixture. Remove Jello from refrigerator, fold into topping until well blended, pour into pan and sprinkle with remaining wafer mixture. Chill several hours.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix sugar and coconut; add condensed milk and melted butter. Roll into balls and chill.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 small pies.

title: nora's peanut butter bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add peanut butter and work into dry ingredients.
Add one egg beaten with milk.
Mix gently; do not beat.
Bake 1 hour in a small loaf pan at 350°. Use straw to test for doneness.
Top usually cracks.

title: two-tone fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients except soda.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until reaches 290° on candy thermometer.
Add baking soda; mix until foams up.
Cool 2 hours, then break into pieces.

title: honey-dijon chicken
directions: Mix honey, mustard, curry powder and soy sauce.
Wash chicken parts; pat dry and place in honey mixture.
Marinate for several hours or overnight.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, and 15 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture is texture of corn meal.
Add cheese and buttermilk.
Roll out or drop into muffin cups.
May add garlic powder to mixture.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nanny raye's best ever chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, milk, egg yolks (save whites for meringue) and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well with whisk.
Cook on medium heat and add butter after mixture becomes warm.
Continue beating with whisk until mixture is very thick.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Peel and slice enough apples to fill quart jar.
Multiply that amount by 6 to fill remaining jars.
As apples are sliced, put them in large bowl with lemon juice and water to keep them from turning brown.
When all are sliced, drain and pack in jars. In large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, spices, salt and water.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over apples. Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
