To make pie, pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add a few pats of butter and cover with crust. Bake as you would any fruit pie.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Place in the bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onions.
Pour soup over this and add beans and corn.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: thump
directions: Boil potatoes; drain.
Add milk and chopped chives (or scallions or spring onions); mash.
Serve with butter.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 3/4 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round or square cake pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Watch closely to not overbake.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely. Frost cake layers and cake with cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup pecans on top.

title: mac 'n' beef soup
directions: Spray 4-quart saucepan with vegetable cooking spray.
Over medium-high heat, heat 1 minute.
Add beef, onion, green pepper, basil and oregano; cook until meat is brown and vegetables are tender, stirring to separate meat.

title: south seas chicken and bananas
directions: In a food processor or blender, blend the lemon juice, condensed milk, milk, coconut and cardamom until smooth.
Pour into a bowl.
Dip bananas into milk mixture.
Roll in cornflake crumbs and set aside.
Dip chicken into remaining milk mixture. Roll in the remaining cornflake crumbs and place in 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Drizzle with 1/2 cup of the melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Arrange bananas over the chicken.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear.
Garnish with kiwi and star fruit, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday cranberry bread
directions: *Can be whole or chopped coarsely.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft.
Drain off remaining water. Add to raisins the applesauce, beaten eggs, sweetener and oil. Mix well.
Blend in soda, flour and spices and salt.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Bake in 9x13-inch greased pan at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza - a dessert!
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar as in making pie crust. Pat into 12-inch
pizza
pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Cool. Cream cheese well;
add
sugar,
mix
well.
Fold
in
whipped cream. Spread over cooled crust.

title: joann's mexican chicken pizza
directions: Spray baking sheet with Pam.
Spray both sides of each tortilla lightly with Pam.
Place tortillas on baking sheet and broil until lightly toasted.
Flip and toast other side.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Mix well to make smooth batter.
Spread on a large, well-greased pan and cover with pared and cored sliced apples.
Other fruit may be used such as peaches. Sprinkle with crushed graham crackers and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: trout bienville
directions: Chop onions and saute in butter.
Add flour to thicken, then the milk.
Heat to a simmer while stirring regularly.
Add shrimp and simmer until the shrimp are done.
Season to taste with cayenne.

title: cucumbers in a bucket
directions: Slice unpeeled cukes.
Place in gallon container.
Add bell pepper and onion; toss.
Combine sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed in bowl or jar; mix well.
Pour over cukes; toss.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
May add more cukes as used.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend ingredients in bowl.
Place in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake for about 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Top will crack. Take from oven and let cool about 10 minutes, then turn out on rack.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in water.
Add frozen orange juice.
Let cool. Add pineapple and oranges.
Let set until firm (use 9 x 13 pan).

title: live longer casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and mushrooms in butter in a large skillet until softened.
Add tomatoes, spinach and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix in pasta.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in raspberries until thawed, then add applesauce. When gelatin sets, spread with sour cream/marshmallow
mixture. Let stand several hours.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Cook chicken 45 minutes to 1 hour. Set aside and cool until meat can be picked.
Save 1 1/2 cups broth.
Melt butter in pan in microwave.
Dump stuffing mix in pan with butter (both seasonings and crumbs).
Stir until moist.

title: lemon snowflake cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg. Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until blended.
Batter will be very sticky.
Drop by teaspoon into confectioner sugar. Roll lightly to coat.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yields 5-6 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts or whole chicken until tender.
Chunk. Combine with cream of mushroom or chicken soup, chopped celery, mayonnaise, chopped onion and blanched almonds.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over frozen spinach (or fresh).
Let water come to boil, turn off heat and let thaw.
Drain and save juice. (Chop if fresh.)
Fold spinach in with 3 hard-boiled, cut up eggs. Pour in ungreased casserole.
Cover with more grated cheese and buttered cornflake crumbs.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: stove-top chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Set aside. Brown chicken in oil. Remove and set aside. Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Saute 4 to 6 minutes. Stir in sauce, tomatoes, sherry, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and noodles.
Heat through. Serve.

title: tempt me truffles
directions: Gradually add 4 cups of powdered sugar to cream cheese, mixing well after each addition.
Add chocolate and vanilla; mix well. Chill several hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts, cocoa or additional powdered sugar.
Chill.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: emu stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Microwave potatoes until soft to the touch (about 7 minutes per potato).
Pan saute emu sausage links on medium-high heat until heated (about 10 minutes).
For a crisp shell, take potatoes out of microwave and place on center rack of oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove potatoes and cut down the middle lengthwise; squeeze both ends to open.
Add butter, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly with fork.
Pour melted cheese over top.
Place sliced emu sausage on top and serve.
This makes a nice meal all by itself or serve with green salad.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine and let set for 2 hours. Drain well.

title: butter fudge fingers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Add nuts.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until top has dull crust. Cool slightly.
Make topping.
Spread on brownies.
When set, cut in 2 x 1-inch fingers.
Makes 32 fingers.

title: grandma cook's refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in large bowl.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour liquid mixture over cucumbers.
When cool, pour mixture into jars or 1 large container.
Set in refrigerator.
In 7 days, pickles are ready to use.
Will keep for months.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine eggs, 2 cups sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Whip on medium-high speed until mixture is doubled in volume (about 1 hour).
While this is being whipped, mix graham cracker crumbs with 1/4 cup sugar and blend in butter with fork or pastry blender.
With back of a spoon, press mixture into bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan to form crust.

title: easy crescent dogs
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cut each cheese slice into 6 strips. Slit hot dogs to within 1/2-inch of ends. Insert 3 strips of cheese into each slit. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles and roll each triangle around each hot dog. Place crescent dogs on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just a little crisp.
Combine potato soup and sour cream.
Add to broccoli and mix.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spiced winter fruit
directions: Arrange first 4 ingredients in layers in an ungreased 3-quart baking dish; set aside.
Pour applesauce in a small saucepan; cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in sherry, cinnamon and nutmeg; pour over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: In large glass bowl, mix margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Repeat 1 to 2 minutes if necessary.
Pour melted mixture over the Crispix.
Stir to coat.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Dump chocolate mixture into a grocery bag.
Add powdered sugar.
Close bag and shake to mix.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meat balls on rice or noodles
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, onion soup mix, 1/2 cup rice and catsup. Make into meat balls.
In a large pan, fry meat balls until brown.

title: hawaiian pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat eggs, one at a time. Alternate milk and dry ingredients.
Bake in large pound cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.
(Sift all-purpose flour 3 times to equal cake flour.)

title: pineapple burgers
directions: Drain pineapple well.
If using pineapple spears, divide meat into 2 patties.
Form around spears.
If using pineapple rings, divide meat into 4 thinner patties; place a ring between 2 patties, sealing edges.
Place burgers on rack 6 inches away from broiler unit; broil 5 minutes.
Turn; broil 5 minutes more.
Pour Spicy Sauce over burgers.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until tender and dry.
Mix all other ingredients and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Will be a little shaky in center when taken out of oven.
Raisins or coconut may be added, if desired.
Delicious.

title: vesta's winter marmalade
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add sugar, cup for cup.
Cook over medium heat until thick. Watch carefully. Do not let stick on bottom. Seal hot.

title: chicken asopao(very thick chicken soup)
directions: Cut chicken in small serving pieces; rub each piece with salt, oregano and garlic.
Brown it in oil, then add ham, onion, tomatoes and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Remove bones from the chicken and put it in the pot.
Add water, capers and olives; cook for 5 minutes.
Add rice; season to taste and simmer until the rice is tender.
Garnish with peas, strips of pimento and grated cheese. The Asopao must be served immediately or it will dry out.

title: green rice
directions: Saute the broccoli, onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients except rice.
Put rice in bottom of buttered casserole. Put mixture on top.
Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes.
Boil potatoes in peeling, then drain and cube. Add 3 teaspoons salt, 6 tablespoons minced onion and 3 teaspoons wine vinegar to warm potatoes and let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Add celery, olives, parsley and mayonnaise.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased loaf pan.
Chopped nuts or dates can be added to batter.
Can be baked in round cans for smaller loaves which make nice gifts.
Adjust baking time.
Freezes well.

title: sausage bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain; stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: beef and barley soup(yields 4 servings)
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in 1 tablespoon oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Add beef broth, thyme and bay leaf to pot.
Bring to boil.
Add 1/2 beef.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Cut remaining beef in 1/4-inch thick slices to use later in Orange Beef.
Add barley, onions and carrots to pot.
Return to boiling.
Lower heat and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Add celery and cook 5 minutes or until tender. Discard bay leaf.
Cool.

title: mom's rice krispies treats
directions: In medium saucepan melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Pour into bowl with Rice Krispies and mix. Pour in glass dish and press down smooth.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: fruited cranberry sauce
directions: Bring juice, honey and orange sections to a boil in a large nonaluminum pot.
Boil 1 minute.
Add pineapple and cranberries. Cook until cranberries pop and mixture thickens slightly.
Ladle into half pint jars and seal.
Makes 5 half pints.

title: *pita with leeks
directions: Cut and wash leeks thoroughly. Drain. Saute in butter until tender. Set aside to cool.

title: chocolate covered balls
directions: Add sugar to crumbs and blend in melted margarine.
Add coconut, nuts and peanut butter.
Blend with hands and shape into small packed balls.
Dip in chocolate, which has been melted over hot water.
Place on wax paper to harden.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sugar until the sugar is melted.
Add the can of Cheerwine, a dash of salt, whipping cream and the cherries, also the juice.
Freeze.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients, except carrots, with mixer.
Mix in carrots
with a spoon.
Bake in rectangular pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut mounds
directions: Melt combined morsels in top of double boiler over boiling water on stove or melt in large bowl in microwave, following manufacturer's directions for melting chocolate.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Dip halved chicken breasts in lemon juice and roll in mixture of pecans, Parmesan, garlic salt and basil.
Saute in 1 tablespoon olive oil until golden brown on both sides.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate meat for 5+ hours (best if overnight), alternating sides.
Grill over medium heat approximately 7 minutes each side.
Can also be used with chicken and seafood.

title: palachintas
directions: Separate egg yolks.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Mix together egg yolks, milk, flour, salt and sugar.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour thin layer into large heated skillet, coated with oil.
Cook until golden brown, then turn over and cook on other side until golden brown.
Fill with favorite filling; for example, apricot, damson preserves.
Put on a plate and eat.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Mix and then form into a loaf.
Put a few bacon slices on top. Pour tomato juice over all.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour. May be pressed into a cake pan and topped with catsup.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients lightly with marshmallows and sour cream or yogurt.
You may serve at once.
Better if made ahead and refrigerated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jo's peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in oven to melt.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar and milk (should be very thin).
When butter is melted, remove from the oven and sprinkle brown sugar over bottom of pan, then pour all the batter into the pan.
Open a can of peaches and spoon the slices evenly all over the pan, then pour remaining syrup all over the batter and peaches.
Sprinkle the cinnamon lightly over the top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken in water which has been seasoned with celery salt, seasoned salt, garlic powder, Accent, salt and pepper. Remove bones from chicken and cut into cubes.
Reserve broth.
In a 5-quart pot, fry sausage and vegetables together.
Add chicken and 4 cups chicken broth.
Taste broth and season, if needed.
It should be a little salty.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice; stir and cover.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.
Do not lift lid.

title: easy cookie
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar.
Add egg, flour and salt.
Roll dough into balls the size of a marble.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Put cherries,
nuts or jelly in center.
Take up with a spatula.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease if any.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix mushroom soup with 2/3 can of water. Pour over meat.
Cover with cheese slices completely.
Place Tater Tots in rows covering cheese completely.
Bake at 350°
for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches.
Put in a bowl and add sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Place peaches in the bottom of a buttered pan.
Spoon Bisquick mixture on top and spread.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: short'nen bread
directions: Cream eggs and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Let cool and serve with jelly or preserves.
Big Mama's recipe will long be remembered.
Born in 1880.
This is how we made it.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toast 1/2 cup coconut.
Set aside. Bake pie shell 8 minutes. Cool slightly.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters and set aside.
Mix liquid from oysters, half and half and 3/4 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce together and set aside.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter and spread 1/3 mixture on bottom of dish.
Put 1/2 of oysters on top of crackers and add 1/2 of milk mixture.
Repeat layer and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.
I usually double or triple this recipe and serve it with holiday dinners.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly.
Make vanilla pudding.
Put 3/4 of peanut butter mixture in bottom of crust.
Pour pudding over.
Spread Dream Whip. Put rest of peanut butter mixture on top and refrigerate.
Better then the Buckhorn Inn's.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: Drain beans, reserving 2/3 cup liquid.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add beans, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir gently to blend and heat until ready to serve.
Transfer with a slotted spoon to a serving bowl.
Top with bacon crumbs.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into greased casserole.
Place casserole in pan of hot water in oven.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 50 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Cook macaroni.
In large skillet, brown hamburger and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cook and let simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.
(Add spices to taste.) Drain macaroni.
Prepare as directed on package.
Add hamburger/sauce mixture to macaroni and cheese.
In large lasagna pan, pour on layer of mixture.
Sprinkle part of Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add another layer of hamburger mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: 3 layer salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Partially congeal and add crushed pineapple; congeal.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Add softened cream cheese.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Chill.
Combine pineapple juice, lemon juice, flour, sugar and eggs in double boiler.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Cool and spread over mixture.
Chill.
Use 3-quart casserole dish.

title: bacon-cheese puffs
directions: Bring milk and butter (cut up) to boil over medium heat.
Add flour all at once and stir until it forms a ball and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time and beat until smooth.
Then add remaining eggs.
Mix well.
Drop onto well-greased foil lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, spices and salt together.
In a gallon jar, layer eggs and onions.
Pour mixture.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks, lemon juice and peel until smooth. Beat egg whites in small mixing bowl until stiff peaks form. Fold beaten egg whites into cream cheese mixture. Spread evenly into prepared crust. I put cherry or blueberry pie filling on after it has chilled for a few hours.

title: shrimp noodle bake
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Combine noodles, sour cream, soup, onion, olives, dill, salt and half of the cheese; mix well.
Fold in shrimp.
Spoon into shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, then sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Pour hot water in shallow bowl and sprinkle gelatin over it. When gelatin is dissolved, stir in warmed tomato juice. Stir in all other ingredients, except cream cheese, and cool in the refrigerator.
Warm cheese until it is spreadable. Spread 1/2 of the mixture. Allow to set until firm and pour remaining 1/2 over top to form aspic, cheese, aspic.
Or put spoonful of cheese in muffin cup, then cover with tomato mixture. Refrigerate until set, several hours.
Garnish with dab of mayonnaise and sprig of mint, if desired.

title: chocolate haystacks
directions: Melt chips, butter and marshmallows. Stir until smooth. Remove from heat, stir in oatmeal, coconut and mix. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Cool baked cake layers.
In small bowl, combine pudding, topping mixes and milk; beat with electric mixer until stiff. Place 1 cake layer, flat side down on serving plate.
Use about 1 cup of pudding mixture and make a ring 1/2 inch high on top of cake.
Fill center of ring with cherry pie filling.
Place second layer on top.
Put remaining mixture on top, then cherry filling. Chill 1 hour.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: candy shop pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Grease baking sheet or pizza pan. Place whole bar of dough scored side down onto prepared baking sheet or pizza pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately sprinkle morsels over hot crust; drop peanut butter by spoonfuls onto morsels. Let stand for 5 minutes or until morsels are shiny. Gently spread chocolate and peanut butter evenly over cookie crust. Sprinkle candy in single layer over pizza. Cut into wedges; serve warm or at room temperature.

title: pineapple salada
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let it cool until it reaches a syrup stage.
Add drained pineapple, bananas and marshmallows to gelatin.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand to congeal.

title: italian meat loaves
directions: Mix ingredients. shape into loaves about 3/4 c. each. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. Top with salsa (your choice) with 1/4 c. brown sugar added. Bake until done (cheese will be bubbling!).

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Boil sugar and cream for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in all at one time the peanut butter, vanilla and soda crackers. Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Prepare jello with hot water.
When dissolved substitute juices for the usual cold water, adding water if needed.
Let jello begin to set.
Mix fruits and when jello is partially set, fold fruits into it.
Place 1/2 of mixture in dish or jello mold. When solidly set, spread with sour cream.
Pour remaining jello mixture over top and chill.

title: toffee candy
directions: Combine the butter and sugar; stir over medium heat until mixture turns a honey color and bubbles make little puffs of smoke (takes 10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Spread onto greased cookie sheets.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
As they melt, spread over top of toffee.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Mix all ingredients and mashed avocados.
Make this recipe the night before and let set in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Over low heat, combine flour and Parkay until smooth.
Add sugar, salt and pepper, then add milk slowly to make white sauce. Stir in both cans of corn and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into mixture.
Pour into shallow pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
In a large skillet saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add picante sauce.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Simmer until melted.
Layer in a large, deep baking dish:
chips, chicken and sauce.
Repeat layers. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fried okra
directions: Rinse okra; drain well and pat dry.
Remove tip and stem ends. Cut okra crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and water in a bowl; stir well.
Add okra.
Toss gently to coat well.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper in a bowl; stir well.
Add okra to cornmeal mixture, a few slices at a time, tossing gently to coat well.
Pour oil to depth of 1-inch in a large heavy skillet.
Heat to 375°.
Fry okra in hot oil over medium heat until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and water and beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon and drain on paper towels.
Cook hamburger and onion in a large skillet until brown.
Drain.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer approximately 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet meatballs and spaghetti(candy)
directions: Mix nuts, oleo, sugar and egg together; cook slowly for 10 minutes, stirring constantly to keep from scorching.
Take off fire.
Add vanilla.
Pour over nuts and Rice Krispies.
Stir well. Grease hands with oleo and roll in small balls, then roll in coconut.
(Put coconut on wax paper or in small bowl.)

title: curry dip (jo sparks)
directions: Combine all ingredients
and put in refrigerator.
Good with raw vegetables, crackers and chips.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add flour and salt.
Beat about 1 minute.
Add cheese; beat another minute. Sprinkle with water; beat until dough begins to come together. Press into a 5-inch square on floured surface.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll dough to 9-inch square.
Cut into 4 equal squares, then cut each square into 8 strips.
Place on ungreased baking sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bake at 400°.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onions and cook until golden yellow.
Stir in sauerkraut and cook for 8 minutes.
Mix in potato and caraway seed.
Pour in the boiling water.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 30 minutes.
Cover and continue cooking 30 minutes longer.
Brown sugar and/or an apple may be added to give different flavor.
Servings:
6 to 8.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, 1/2 cup cold water and blueberries until mixture thickens.
Add lemon juice, butter and stir in the rest of the berries.
Pour into baked pie crust and chill.
When cool, beat about one pint of whipping cream and top pie.

title: honey crunch bars
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Put butter, honey, brown sugar and cinnamon into 3-quart saucepan.
Stir constantly; bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add noodles and stir.
Add nuts.
Put into square pan and press down. Let stand 1 hour before cutting.
Cut into bars.

title: mooers chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in water 2-inches over the top of the beans.
Simmer the beans, covered, until tender.
Add tomatoes, juice and all.
Saute in a separate pan: green peppers, onions and garlic in salad oil.
Add parsley.
In separate pan, melt butter and brown meat.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add meat mixture to beans, add remaining spices and simmer, covered, for 1 hour, then uncovered for 30 minutes.
Skim fat.
If too thick, you can add tomato juice or V-8.
This makes a big batch.
Freezes very well.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine reserved pineapple juice, soy sauce and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add oil.
Add chicken and garlic; stir-fry until chicken is white, about 4 minutes.
Remove chicken from wok with slotted spoon.
Add red pepper; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add pineapple juice mixture; cook and stir until thickened, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Add reserved pineapple, chicken, vegetables and wheat germ.
Cook until heated through. Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon surprise
directions: Mix all ingredients. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture. Pour into buttered muffin tins. Set in pan of water and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: olive nut sandwich filling
directions: Blend well the cream cheese and mayonnaise, then add the remaining ingredients (no salt).
Mix well.
Serve on party rye or make little finger sandwiches.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Lightly grease baking dish; arrange chicken breasts and top with cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle stuffing mix on top, then drizzle butter over chicken. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix squash, oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Slowly add dry ingredients to squash mixture.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and empty from pans.

title: cajun moc c hue
directions: Put peanut oil and butter in heated skillet.
Add all chopped veggies and corn that has been shaved from cob.
Stir over moderate heat until tender.

title: baked chicken
directions: In baking pan, place chopped onion with peel, garlic with peel, tomatoes, celery, carrots and water.
Salt and pepper chicken; place on top of ingredients in baking pan and bake 45 to 60 minutes in 375° oven.
After 20 minutes, baste with beer. Baste every 1/2 hour.
Melt butter in saucepan; add sifted flour until it makes a paste.
Remove chicken from pan.
Strain stock into a bowl.
Discard used vegetables; reheat stock and add to flour paste slowly until thick and creamy.
Serve as a gravy over chicken.

title: raisin rolls
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients.
Spoon out on board and roll into shape.
Needs no baking.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel and grate cucumber.
Mix with other ingredients until well blended.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with raw vegetables of your choice.

title: refrigerator rolls(easy)
directions: Soften Crisco in hot water.
Add sugar and salt, cool to 115°. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add egg.
Mix together well and add flour.
Beat well.
Place in refrigerator to chill (dough will be soft until it chills).
Make out one hour before baking or long enough for dough to double.
I place a pat of butter on roll and fold over.
This melts as it cooks.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake dough as needed.
Keeps in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and mixed vegetables, stirring good. Mix in cooked chicken; put in baking dish. Mix stuffing according to package. Add margarine. Put on top of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla, salt and egg.
Stir together until real creamy.
Mix in milk, then mix in flour and baking powder.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture on bottom and up sides about halfway.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, except spinach together.
Add the spinach that has been thoroughly drained. Squeeze all liquid out with your hands.

title: eclairs
directions: Prepare pudding with skim milk.
Add sour cream.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker lined casserole. Soften chocolate frosting one minute in microwave,
then spread over pudding.
Top with more whipped topping if desired.
Chill. This is a low fat, low sugar delicious dessert.

title: texas beans rice
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Combine beans, water, ham hock, onion, garlic and salt in large Dutch oven.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat to medium and cook 45 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove meat from ham hocks and return meat to beans.

title: topping for german chocolate cake
directions: Cook until thickened.
Add 1 1/3 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spread on cake.

title: roast pork with currant jelly glaze
directions: Place roast, lean side down on rack in open roasting pan. Insert meat thermometer so bulb is in thickest part of roast, not touching fat.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer reaches an internal temperature of 170°.
While roast is cooking prepare glaze.

title: pattie's pineapple casserole
directions: Mix 3 tablespoons pineapple, flour and sugar.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture and cheese.
Crush Ritz crackers on top.
Pour over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: finger salads
directions: Press crescent roll mix onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: indoor s'mores
directions: Melt 5 c. marshmallows, corn syrup, butter and chocolate chips in microwave about 4 min. or until melted; stir in 1 tsp. vanilla and add 8 c. of Golden Grahams cereal.
Stir thoroughly, then add 1 cup of mini marshmallows and put in a buttered 9 by 13 in. pan to cool.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
When slightly jelled, add pineapple, nuts and pie filling.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla and spread over top of jelled salad.

title: pecan or almond tastees
directions: Dough:
Mix and chill.
Yield:
8 dozen small tarts or 4 dozen muffin-size tarts.

title: bill's mashed potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and boil until done.
Drain off all water.
Add 1/2 stick of butter.
Add milk to mashed potatoes according to your preference of consistency.
Add Mrs. Dash original seasoning. Add Jane's Krazy salt.
Blend together and season to taste.
Add more milk and butter if you like your potatoes (moist) loose.
You may also add 5 tablespoons of gravy for more flavor.

title: best cake ever
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake yellow cake as directed and cool completely.
Place pineapple and sugar in small pan and boil 5 minutes, then cool.
Punch holes in cake with a fork, then top with pineapple glaze.
Mix pudding and milk, then pour over pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with coconut and nuts.
Chill completely.

title: confetti bean soup mix(a great gift)
directions: Up to 1 Month Before Using:
In a large bowl, mix beans. Spoon into four 4-cup containers, placing about three rounded cupfuls in each.

title: cream of potato soup(made from leftover mashed potatoes)
directions: In heavy stew pan, melt butter; add onion, saute until light golden.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add whole milk and mashed potatoes.
Stir until mixed.
Heat until almost boiling.
Serve immediately.

title: salmon spread(appetizer)
directions: Mix cream cheese, grated onion, lemon juice, horseradish, salt and pepper in medium bowl until blended.
Finely flake salmon. Add to mixture and stir until smooth and creamy.
Spoon into crock or serving bowl.
Garnish with green onion.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 cups. Serve with assorted crackers or garlic toast.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
In bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, cocoa, sugar and butter; press evenly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: broccoli and onion casserole
directions: Cook in saucepan soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper for 1 minute. In casserole dish, layer broccoli, soup mixture and 1/2 can onions. Bake 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Add remaining onions and cook 5 minutes.

title: nut balls
directions: Mix in that order.
Roll into small balls.
Bake in oven at 375° for about 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool real well. Shake a few at a time in bag with confectioners sugar.
Makes 65.
